1
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:13,847
- Hyuk-joon, who was all about Hyun-seo…
- That's right.

2
00:00:13,930 --> 00:00:17,684
…said, "Maybe I can open myself up more,"
and that's where we left things.

3
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:20,562
- Oh, no.
- That was a little disappointing.

4
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:22,981
- It's really disheartening.
- It's a letdown.

5
00:00:23,064 --> 00:00:26,776
Because Hyun-seo seemed to have
made up her mind about Hyuk-joon,

6
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:27,861
then this happens.

7
00:00:27,944 --> 00:00:29,112
Totally. That's right.

8
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:32,157
You know, I started watching
<i>Single's Inferno </i>last week.

9
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:33,450
Oh!

10
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:36,953
The panelists were all very supportive
of their contestants.

11
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:37,871
- Ah.
- Mmm.

12
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:40,415
- So I think I'm gonna try that.
- You'll be supportive?

13
00:00:40,498 --> 00:00:43,209
Well, at least for this episode…
for this one.

14
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:46,087
I promise to make an effort
to be more supportive.

15
00:00:46,171 --> 00:00:47,130
Mmm.

16
00:00:47,213 --> 00:00:48,423
And that means I'll be supportive

17
00:00:48,506 --> 00:00:50,800
even when it comes to Hyuk-joon's
shallow, shallow behavior.

18
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:53,136
- Okay. I give you ten minutes.
- Okay.

19
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:56,264
Ahn Seung-hyun's loyalties
constantly shift around,

20
00:00:56,347 --> 00:00:57,891
but I'm sure he has his reasons.

21
00:00:57,974 --> 00:01:00,727
- He is shifty like that.
- Wow. This is so unnatural.

22
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:02,604
- I understand. And I love you.
- That's right.

23
00:01:02,687 --> 00:01:03,980
I do, Ahn Seung-hyun.

24
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:12,363
What's next? This is six,
shouldn't we go to number one?

25
00:01:13,281 --> 00:01:15,742
Oh, so they're still
on the Rotation Dates.

26
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:18,286
LOUNGE ANNEX

27
00:01:18,369 --> 00:01:19,704
Jae-seo.

28
00:01:21,831 --> 00:01:23,208
No, we're not killing bugs again.

29
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:26,002
- Seriously. Don't do that.
- Is that the tissue he used to squish it?

30
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:27,921
Now--

31
00:01:28,004 --> 00:01:30,507
At this rate, the alliances
are just going to keep forming and--

32
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:32,050
No way. No.

33
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:35,261
- We need to show our serious sides.
- Hmm.

34
00:01:35,345 --> 00:01:36,930
But I am serious, though.

35
00:01:37,514 --> 00:01:40,517
We came to find a relationship,
not to make people laugh.

36
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,269
That's a fair point.
I do want to find someone to date.

37
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:44,270
Exactly.

38
00:01:44,354 --> 00:01:46,314
But since these are Rotation Dates…

39
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:49,692
I'm really looking forward to this.
Hey, put on some cologne.

40
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:52,153
Why? It's not like the cologne
can override my personality.

41
00:01:52,237 --> 00:01:54,823
No, I'm telling you. A scent…
A scent gives you a certain power.

42
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:55,782
I hear you, but…

43
00:01:55,865 --> 00:01:58,243
No, listen to him, Jae-seo.

44
00:02:06,292 --> 00:02:07,669
Who is it?

45
00:02:09,546 --> 00:02:10,880
Oh, hello.

46
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:12,882
- Oh, hello.
- Oh!

47
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:14,342
LOUNGE ANNEX
JAE-SEO - SEO-YOON

48
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:18,263
I hope they have
a deeper conversation this time. Please.

49
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:20,306
I know. He just needs to go for it.

50
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,600
He has to express himself.
He has to let her know.

51
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:25,854
Are you really cold enough
for two hand warmers?

52
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,314
Oh, no. These have gone cold.

53
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:31,401
Even though we've talked before,

54
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:36,114
Seo-yoon and I haven't really had
the chance to talk for very long.

55
00:02:36,197 --> 00:02:40,118
We've never talked about anything
of substance or importance.

56
00:02:40,201 --> 00:02:43,830
So I really wanted to have
a conversation with her the most.

57
00:02:45,081 --> 00:02:47,500
- This really is his chance.
- Yes.

58
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:49,794
How was your day?

59
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:50,795
- Today?
- Yeah.

60
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:52,881
It was…

61
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:55,717
- Rough?
- Oh, rough? No, no, it wasn't rough.

62
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,969
- Oh, I see.
- It was a bit… How do I say this?

63
00:02:58,887 --> 00:03:02,348
Me and my roomie get along really well,
so we talk a lot.

64
00:03:02,432 --> 00:03:03,683
- Yeah, I noticed.
- Right?

65
00:03:03,766 --> 00:03:06,769
But we always end up
staying up pretty late.

66
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:10,899
And I think the fatigue that has been
building up just kind of hit me today,

67
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:13,484
like, all at once, like, "Bang!"

68
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:15,904
Do I look like I'm tired?

69
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:17,488
- Huh? No.
- Really? That's a relief.

70
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:19,657
- Why's that?
- I'm kinda forcing my eyes open.

71
00:03:19,741 --> 00:03:21,868
- Whoa. Hey, you don't have to do that.
- I mean…

72
00:03:21,951 --> 00:03:24,579
- Well, uh…
- I'm not sure you have to go that far.

73
00:03:24,662 --> 00:03:26,080
- Well, that's a relief.
- Right. No.

74
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:28,499
I mean, you don't need
to go that far for my sake.

75
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:29,584
Oh. Oh, oh…

76
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:32,170
I'm saying, it's worse to pretend
you're not tired when you are.

77
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:36,466
If you say you're tired, and I think,
"Why is she tired? Is she upset?"

78
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:38,468
Then wouldn't I be the weird one?

79
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:39,928
- Right?
- Exactly.

80
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:41,638
- Right?
- It should be the other way around.

81
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:43,556
- Wow. That's a huge load off my back.
- For sure.

82
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:46,476
I really need to start thinking
that way more often.

83
00:03:46,559 --> 00:03:48,019
Thank you.

84
00:03:48,102 --> 00:03:51,064
- He really is nicer to Seo-yoon.
- He's a good listener.

85
00:03:51,147 --> 00:03:53,191
So, I also talk to my roommate a lot,

86
00:03:53,274 --> 00:03:56,819
and, uh, he mentioned
that you're really into healthy people.

87
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:59,822
- This is the thing he should bring up.
- He hinted that was your type.

88
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:02,283
Oh, so with me, I…
No, no, no, that's not it.

89
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:04,744
I, uh, went for a physical recently,

90
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:06,788
and it turns out
I have an iron deficiency.

91
00:04:06,871 --> 00:04:08,790
My liver enzymes were off or something.

92
00:04:08,873 --> 00:04:11,542
But I just ignored it, thinking,
"I'm still young, so whatever."

93
00:04:11,626 --> 00:04:13,544
- But they actually called me--
- Not so young anymore.

94
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:15,880
Oh, God. Did I just…

95
00:04:15,964 --> 00:04:18,007
You're right, I'm not young anymore.

96
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:19,092
That's so sad, though.

97
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:21,511
I totally get it. I remember feeling
the same way at your age.

98
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:23,930
- You know what I mean, right? Right?
- This isn't progressing.

99
00:04:24,013 --> 00:04:26,599
So we're at a doctor's office now?

100
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:28,476
- I guess I should get going.
- What? Why?

101
00:04:28,559 --> 00:04:30,019
- That was quick.
- Oh, and that's why…

102
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:30,937
TIME IS UP

103
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:32,313
Right. Anyway…

104
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:34,649
Well, time to go. This was fun.

105
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:38,945
Ah, thus ends another… yes,
another encounter with meaningless banter.

106
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:42,031
- Jesus, what even was that?
- They had so much potential.

107
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:45,535
So essentially, he's gained nothing
from this encounter.

108
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:47,578
- Nothing.
- He knows she has an iron deficiency.

109
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:50,206
- Her liver levels are off.
- That's what he got out of it.

110
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:53,626
It started off so well.

111
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:07,098
When it comes to looks,
Seo-yoon is the closest to my ideal woman.

112
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:10,226
But I think it's so much more important
what's on the inside.

113
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:14,605
I chose her for my first impression vote
pretty much based on her looks,

114
00:05:14,689 --> 00:05:17,608
but we still haven't been able
to have a real conversation.

115
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:19,610
I mean, she was my top pick.

116
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:23,906
I'm disappointed I haven't been able
to learn more about her as a person.

117
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:27,035
Come on.

118
00:05:27,118 --> 00:05:29,537
This must be so frustrating for Jae-seo.
Don't you think?

119
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:32,332
It's possible that his feelings
for Seo-yoon could grow,

120
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:34,667
since they haven't had
a real conversation yet.

121
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:38,212
It seems like Jae-seo's being
more careful with her now

122
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:39,964
that his feelings for her have grown.

123
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:41,674
- He really is.
- Right.

124
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:44,719
At this point in the process,
this isn't necessarily a bad thing.

125
00:05:44,802 --> 00:05:46,012
Being considerate.

126
00:05:46,095 --> 00:05:48,222
But today's tiny little date
was just too short.

127
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:49,724
- Not nearly long enough.
- Absolutely.

128
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:50,892
POST OFFICE

129
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:52,560
The Post Office. Who is it?

130
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:54,979
It's Jung-yun.

131
00:05:57,106 --> 00:05:59,525
- Uh. Hey, there.
- Hello, hello.

132
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:00,610
Who's there?

133
00:06:00,693 --> 00:06:01,819
That's right. We're the same age.

134
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:03,446
- Su-ji.
- We're the same age.

135
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:05,531
I honestly thought you were
a little bit older than me.

136
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:07,241
- Oh, yeah?
- I'm surprised we're the same age.

137
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:09,369
- You thought I was older?
- Uh-huh.

138
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:11,454
- I thought you were older.
- Jung-yun likes Su-ji.

139
00:06:11,537 --> 00:06:13,831
They voted for each other
for Sparks House.

140
00:06:13,915 --> 00:06:16,250
I was so nervous and so excited.

141
00:06:16,334 --> 00:06:19,337
I've been yearning
for the chance to talk to Su-ji.

142
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:22,256
She's the one I'm most excited to talk to.

143
00:06:24,675 --> 00:06:27,387
I haven't really talked
to Jung-yun very much.

144
00:06:28,096 --> 00:06:31,015
He was my top pick
for the first impression vote.

145
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:34,060
And then I picked the metronome
right from the start,

146
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:36,437
because I thought that it belonged to him.

147
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:39,482
But then it turned out that it wasn't his.

148
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:44,112
So I was really happy
to have an opportunity to talk to him.

149
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:46,155
This is good. Get this ball rolling.

150
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:50,034
I really just…

151
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:53,621
I really wanted the chance to talk.

152
00:06:53,704 --> 00:06:54,997
- Oh, with me?
- Mm-hmm.

153
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:58,042
When we first met, you gave me the…
your first impression vote.

154
00:06:58,126 --> 00:07:00,628
- Oh, right. I gave you the towel.
- Right, the towel, so…

155
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:01,712
That's right.

156
00:07:03,172 --> 00:07:04,674
I also wanted to…

157
00:07:05,174 --> 00:07:07,009
talk to you, but never got the chance,

158
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:09,554
so I checked out your diary
at the 5 Minute Library.

159
00:07:09,637 --> 00:07:10,972
- Oh, really?
- Good, good.

160
00:07:11,055 --> 00:07:11,889
This is great.

161
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:14,934
I was like, "If this is what it takes
to learn about him, so be it!"

162
00:07:15,017 --> 00:07:17,228
- Wow.
- "If this is what it takes, here we go."

163
00:07:17,311 --> 00:07:18,855
You said it was an easy read.

164
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:20,481
- Yeah. So, um…
- Was I really an easy read?

165
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:24,527
Well, the reason it was such an easy read
is that we have a lot in common,

166
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:26,988
like the fact that we're both homebodies.

167
00:07:27,071 --> 00:07:27,947
Oh.

168
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:29,991
Whoa, what's this?

169
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:35,371
She told me that she read my diary
at the 5 Minute Library.

170
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:38,458
She also mentioned earlier
that it was an easy read,

171
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:40,877
earlier, while we were all
sitting at the table.

172
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:43,254
Hmm, I think I read
about three-fourths of it.

173
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:44,422
Oh?

174
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:47,008
- Did you retain anything?
- Mmm.

175
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:48,092
Oh…

176
00:07:48,176 --> 00:07:50,136
Ah, so she really committed it to memory.

177
00:07:50,219 --> 00:07:53,389
At the time, I couldn't stop
wondering about who it was.

178
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:57,643
So to find out that it was me all along
was a little…

179
00:07:58,603 --> 00:08:02,023
I'd be lying if I told you
it didn't give me butterflies.

180
00:08:02,106 --> 00:08:04,692
So, yeah, it gave me butterflies.

181
00:08:07,403 --> 00:08:10,072
He's so happy he could die.

182
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:13,659
Ah.

183
00:08:15,536 --> 00:08:18,331
You should also know
that I only picked the metronome today

184
00:08:18,414 --> 00:08:19,749
because I thought it belonged to you.

185
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:20,750
Oh, really?

186
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,002
So I was like, "Oh, thank God,
I got the metronome."

187
00:08:23,085 --> 00:08:26,464
But then, when she said,
"This <i>Art of </i>whatever, whose is it?"

188
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:28,049
- That's mine.
- You said, "It's mine."

189
00:08:28,132 --> 00:08:32,428
So I was just floored, like, that yours
was actually the eternal singles' book.

190
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:33,846
- So that went well for me.
- Right.

191
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:36,140
- This is how you express yourself.
- You do.

192
00:08:36,224 --> 00:08:38,059
So, I did pick you
for my first impression vote.

193
00:08:38,142 --> 00:08:39,435
Mm-hmm. That's right. Uh-huh.

194
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:42,188
But then I couldn't even talk to you,
the person I voted for.

195
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:45,107
- Right. Yes.
- So I was getting pretty frustrated.

196
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,777
So when I was doing my interviews,

197
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:51,572
since you picked me, they asked
what the most memorable moment was…

198
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:52,573
Did you even have one?

199
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:55,243
Well, I told them
it was when you gave me the towel.

200
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:56,410
"Her giving me the towel"?

201
00:08:56,494 --> 00:08:58,621
They asked me if we had any interactions.

202
00:08:58,704 --> 00:09:01,374
I was like, "No, none whatsoever.
None at all."

203
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:04,585
But then, they asked me who I would choose

204
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:07,880
if I could pick anyone
to go on a one-on-one date tomorrow.

205
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:11,050
Yes, now's the time.
Express yourself, Jung-yun.

206
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:14,595
I told them that I wanted to talk to you.

207
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:16,764
- Huh, I told them the same thing.
- Oh, really?

208
00:09:16,847 --> 00:09:18,057
Oh, that was smooth.

209
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:21,352
This date's too short!
They should meet up again later tonight.

210
00:09:21,435 --> 00:09:24,564
Talking to Jung-yun really opened my eyes.

211
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:27,525
He was charming in really unexpected ways.

212
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:29,318
I was pleasantly surprised.

213
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:32,488
This is all developing very nicely for me.

214
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:35,533
Su-ji and Jung-yun seem to be
making the most out of this short date.

215
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:37,827
- They really are.
- Bad news.

216
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:38,744
YOUR TIME IS UP

217
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:39,954
Then I'll tell you mine later.

218
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:41,205
Ten minutes is so short.

219
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:44,083
Listen, if there's any chance
you wanted to talk more…

220
00:09:46,335 --> 00:09:48,629
…would you, like, ask to see me?

221
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:50,089
- Huh?
- What?

222
00:09:50,172 --> 00:09:51,215
Hey.

223
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:53,217
- Time out.
- Hold on.

224
00:09:54,135 --> 00:09:56,554
They were, like, really making progress
for a second.

225
00:09:57,263 --> 00:09:59,849
Is saying, "Can we talk again?"
that difficult?

226
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:01,726
- I mean…
- Why does he keep doing that?

227
00:10:01,809 --> 00:10:03,936
- This part isn't easy for them.
- What do you think?

228
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:06,397
- Conversations--
- Would you ask to see me? What do you say?

229
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:08,316
"You do the asking!"

230
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:09,900
Seriously, this is a little…

231
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:12,361
I honestly think
that's how I would respond.

232
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:13,946
Man, he was doing so well.

233
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:16,157
He could've just ended with,
"Can I ask to see you?"

234
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,158
Totally.

235
00:10:17,241 --> 00:10:19,619
- But it was, "Would you ask to see me?"
- Huh? What?

236
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:22,413
He dug his own grave,
and then he stepped right into it.

237
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:24,165
- Jesus Christ.
- This is just way too…

238
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:27,460
…would you, like, ask to see me?

239
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:35,343
- I think I will.
- Yeah?

240
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:37,303
Why? Do you want me to ask to see you?

241
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:40,181
Oh, I would really love it if you did.

242
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:41,557
Yeah?

243
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:43,309
- Then later, I'll…
- Later?

244
00:10:43,392 --> 00:10:45,603
- I think ten minutes is too short.
- It's short. So, later.

245
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:47,480
- Later, then. See you later.
- I'll ask you later.

246
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:49,815
- "See you later." Su-ji, you better!
- Okay, I'm off.

247
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:51,192
Oh, you should be commended

248
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:53,861
merely for holding
a normal conversation, Jung-yun.

249
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:58,032
Ten minutes really was way too short.

250
00:10:58,115 --> 00:11:01,327
I wish I hadn't been so nervous
when I was talking to her,

251
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:04,288
because out of the six, uh,

252
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:08,918
she was the one I'd been looking forward
to talking to more than anyone else.

253
00:11:09,001 --> 00:11:13,297
I think I'm going to try to create
an opportunity to talk to her one-on-one.

254
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:19,470
Now, the Sparks House
members are starting to gather.

255
00:11:19,553 --> 00:11:21,889
Oh, right.
They have to go back to the Sparks House.

256
00:11:27,228 --> 00:11:29,021
- Huh?
- Oh.

257
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:30,648
- I thought you were asleep.
- You're back.

258
00:11:30,731 --> 00:11:32,233
- What are you doing?
- Oh, lying down?

259
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:33,818
- I was just a little tired.
- Oh, really?

260
00:11:33,901 --> 00:11:36,153
The last person Seung-hyun
was interested in was Su--

261
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:38,030
It's Su-ji right now.

262
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:39,240
Was it a good talk?

263
00:11:39,323 --> 00:11:40,950
- Uh-huh.
- How'd it go?

264
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:42,576
- Tell me everything…
- About what?

265
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:43,911
…about talking to Soo-hyun.

266
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:46,414
- Well, we…
- Mmm?

267
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:49,917
…di-didn't really click
as much as I thought we would, so…

268
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,669
- Really?
- Mmm.

269
00:11:51,752 --> 00:11:53,254
- Not at all?
- Mmm.

270
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:54,714
Was that kind of unexpected?

271
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:56,424
Soo-hyun got his first impression vote.

272
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:57,341
That's right.

273
00:11:57,425 --> 00:12:01,762
Well, I'm not really…
When it comes to conversations…

274
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:06,976
I'm not very good at leading them,
so when the other person leads the--

275
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:09,979
Don't you think you should be
the one leading the conversation?

276
00:12:12,022 --> 00:12:13,774
I should lead the conversation,
but I don't--

277
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:16,569
- Why are you swallowing so hard?
- I don't… I don't…

278
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:18,654
- So I want someone else to take the lead.
- Huh? Ah.

279
00:12:18,738 --> 00:12:21,574
But that doesn't seem
like something she's going to do.

280
00:12:21,657 --> 00:12:23,993
Since that's what
I was hoping for initially, I--

281
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:26,245
Oh, you thought Soo-hyun
would take the lead and stuff?

282
00:12:26,328 --> 00:12:27,788
Uh-huh. Mm-hmm.

283
00:12:28,622 --> 00:12:29,999
Hmm…

284
00:12:33,335 --> 00:12:36,797
So during the, uh,
ten-minute conversations today…

285
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:40,634
- Well, I…
- Mmm?

286
00:12:43,345 --> 00:12:46,265
Th-The conversations I had with you
were the only…

287
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:49,351
ones that stuck with me.

288
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:50,352
Oh, really?

289
00:12:50,436 --> 00:12:52,146
They were the most fun.

290
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:54,982
- Thanks.
- They were fun and enjoyable, so…

291
00:12:56,150 --> 00:13:01,614
I guess I'm wondering if maybe you might
have also enjoyed talking to me too.

292
00:13:01,697 --> 00:13:03,199
- Do you--
- I had fun too.

293
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:06,827
Y-You know, maybe you find me fun or…

294
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:10,498
Wait. What do you mean exactly?

295
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:13,459
You know, do you think I'm fun or…

296
00:13:15,127 --> 00:13:19,632
Or is it… that enough for there to be
some romantic attraction?

297
00:13:19,715 --> 00:13:21,008
Oh. You mean me?

298
00:13:21,091 --> 00:13:23,594
Yeah, th-that's what I was wondering.

299
00:13:23,677 --> 00:13:25,054
Hmm…

300
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:28,015
Okay, so…

301
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:31,060
if I'm being completely honest…

302
00:13:35,439 --> 00:13:36,899
Hmm…

303
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:38,776
I kind of…

304
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:42,530
Okay. Do you remember
when we talked up there at the foot bath?

305
00:13:42,613 --> 00:13:43,447
Uh-huh.

306
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:45,199
I said I was developing
an attraction to you.

307
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,161
Until the dancing part,

308
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:51,664
I didn't have specific feelings,
just, "We've gotten really close."

309
00:13:51,747 --> 00:13:52,748
Oh, really?

310
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:54,625
But then, when we were talking up there,

311
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:58,629
I learned so many new things about you
and realized we have so much in common,

312
00:13:58,712 --> 00:14:02,341
so I thought maybe I was starting
to develop an attraction.

313
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:05,261
But it's my first time
experiencing all this.

314
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:06,345
Oh, really?

315
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:09,515
I honestly thought
you weren't into me, like, at all.

316
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:12,476
That's why I asked you that.

317
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:14,979
But anyway, I…

318
00:14:17,773 --> 00:14:20,150
I'm attracted to you, kinda…

319
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:22,027
- Oh, I see.
- Uh, yeah.

320
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,362
Oh.

321
00:14:23,445 --> 00:14:24,446
Oh, my.

322
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:27,408
Wow, Seung-hyun's
finally expressing himself.

323
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:30,870
Look how surprised she is right now.

324
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:35,916
So you're just coming right out
and saying it?

325
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,960
What is this?

326
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:40,796
So you're okay with it,
just coming right with it?

327
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,549
- I kind of thought I wasn't your top pick.
- Oh, I--

328
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:45,467
Well, you kept avoiding eye…

329
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,011
avoiding eye contact with me.

330
00:14:47,094 --> 00:14:48,095
- Oh, my. Oh, my.
- Oh!

331
00:14:48,178 --> 00:14:50,890
I thought you were being reticent
about me intentionally.

332
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:52,933
And I didn't want things to be like that.

333
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:56,145
- Could this…
- Wait. So she is attracted to him.

334
00:14:56,228 --> 00:14:58,647
Yeah. So that's why I was like…

335
00:14:58,731 --> 00:14:59,732
You know… To you…

336
00:14:59,815 --> 00:15:00,983
SPARKS HOUSE

337
00:15:03,819 --> 00:15:05,779
Oh, really? He had to arrive right now?

338
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:07,698
- I'm so exhausted.
- Exhausted?

339
00:15:07,781 --> 00:15:09,158
Ugh. You, get out!

340
00:15:10,618 --> 00:15:12,620
Please step out for just a minute. Please.

341
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:14,079
So it's over now, right?

342
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:17,166
That's it? Would it kill them
to take the conversation outside?

343
00:15:17,249 --> 00:15:19,585
At least they talked about
the most important thing.

344
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:20,920
But, hey, at least it seems

345
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:23,881
the ever-fickle Seung-hyun
has completely made up his mind.

346
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:24,798
I know, right?

347
00:15:24,882 --> 00:15:28,052
Before, it was like
he found his dream woman after every date.

348
00:15:28,135 --> 00:15:31,597
But now, he straight up told Su-ji
that she's his top pick.

349
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:34,475
This is almost like… how do I put this?
To those guys…

350
00:15:34,558 --> 00:15:36,185
It's basically a marriage proposal.

351
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:38,020
Exactly. It requires that much courage.

352
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:39,813
- Exactly.
- It's just insane.

353
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:41,649
But what did you think
of Su-ji's response?

354
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,776
I thought Su-ji had given up
on Seung-hyun,

355
00:15:43,859 --> 00:15:45,027
but judging by her response…

356
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:46,695
- Exactly.
- I know, right?

357
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:49,156
- God, I don't know.
- I'm in the dark on this one.

358
00:15:49,239 --> 00:15:50,366
What are you guys up to?

359
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:52,618
Us? Talking about
how our ten-minute dates went.

360
00:15:52,701 --> 00:15:53,869
Yep. That's right.

361
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:57,623
Today, uh, while you were making
your ten-minute rounds,

362
00:15:57,706 --> 00:16:00,542
did anyone straight up tell you
that they're attracted to you?

363
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:01,460
Whoa. What?

364
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:04,088
I got, "I wanted to talk to you,"
but not, "I'm attracted to you."

365
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,464
- Oh, really?
- Mmm.

366
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:06,715
What about you?

367
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:08,676
- No "I'm attracted to you."
- You didn't get that?

368
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:10,219
- Did you?
- I did.

369
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:11,720
- Whoa!
- Really?

370
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,347
I'm sorry, is he bragging right now?

371
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:15,307
Oh, so are you an alpha male now?

372
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:18,310
- No, no, I'm practically a ga-gamma--
- We have an alpha male among us.

373
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:19,728
Very gamma male right now.

374
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:21,063
What are you talking about?

375
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:23,899
- You're a power-alpha. You're an alpha.
- "Gamma," he says.

376
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:26,402
But that's why I'm struggling.
I'm not that guy.

377
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:28,779
- Never in my life have I ever--
- I say be confident.

378
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:30,572
Enjoy the moment.

379
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:33,158
But how many people
said they were attracted to you?

380
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:34,994
- "How many?"
- How many?

381
00:16:35,077 --> 00:16:36,537
- More than one?
- Yeah.

382
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:38,747
- Whoa. No way.
- Really?

383
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:40,416
Whoa, it's Soo-hyun.

384
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,668
- I wanted to tell you I was grateful.
- For what?

385
00:16:42,751 --> 00:16:46,005
I wanted to thank you for everything
that happened during the paintball game.

386
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:48,173
So I figured I'd try to talk to you.

387
00:16:48,257 --> 00:16:50,384
Oh, and I looked at your diary
at the 5 Minute Library.

388
00:16:50,467 --> 00:16:52,803
- Oh, you chose mine?
- Uh-huh. I looked through that.

389
00:16:52,886 --> 00:16:54,888
And then with the personal items
from earlier…

390
00:16:54,972 --> 00:16:56,974
You know,
since you're majoring in architecture…

391
00:16:57,057 --> 00:16:58,434
Right, right. Oh, the mouse?

392
00:16:58,517 --> 00:17:01,437
Right. So I figured
you obviously work with CAD, so…

393
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,647
- You have a good time?
- Soo-hyun and Han-ju.

394
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:05,482
- Has anything changed at all?
- Still…

395
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:08,068
- They even went on that date.
- Nothing's really changed.

396
00:17:08,152 --> 00:17:11,947
Basically, I'm interested in two people.
You and one other person.

397
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:14,742
You and I got to go on that date earlier,

398
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:16,952
but I haven't had a chance
to talk to the other guy yet.

399
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:19,496
Oh. Then who do you think
is interested in you?

400
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:21,081
- I don't think anyone is.
- Out of the men.

401
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:24,793
Well, I really only care
about the men I'm interested in, so--

402
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:28,505
- Oh, you don't really care who's into you?
- No, no. I really don't. No.

403
00:17:30,174 --> 00:17:32,926
So they directly expressed
their feelings, just like that.

404
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:35,304
So that's what I'm really struggling with.

405
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:37,514
Do I put more effort
toward the person I want to approach…

406
00:17:37,598 --> 00:17:38,432
So they're different?

407
00:17:38,515 --> 00:17:40,309
…or toward the person approaching me?

408
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:42,061
- Different people?
- No way!

409
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:44,021
That's insane.
This is seriously crazy. Oops.

410
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:46,690
I was headed one way,
but she came out of left field so…

411
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:48,442
Mm-hmm…

412
00:17:49,693 --> 00:17:52,863
WHO IS THE PERSON
YOU WANT TO APPROACH?

413
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:54,364
I think it's Su-ji.

414
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:56,992
From the beginning,
I've always had this thought

415
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:59,661
that I should have
a one-on-one conversation with her

416
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:02,289
or that I wanted to get closer to her.

417
00:18:02,372 --> 00:18:03,791
But I was starting to get bummed out

418
00:18:03,874 --> 00:18:06,752
because we've barely had
any opportunities to talk.

419
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:10,672
But now that we're in Sparks House,
we get to spend a lot of time together.

420
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:14,426
And now that there's actually
a possibility of becoming closer,

421
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:16,512
she's moved up to my top pick, I think.

422
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:19,556
- So get to know them all.
- Huh?

423
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:22,601
The ones you're interested in,
and the ones who are approaching you.

424
00:18:22,684 --> 00:18:23,602
Get to know all of them.

425
00:18:23,685 --> 00:18:25,479
That's a good way
to stay eternally single.

426
00:18:25,562 --> 00:18:28,232
Su-ji's totally clueless, huh?

427
00:18:28,315 --> 00:18:30,400
Then what is your heart telling you?

428
00:18:31,068 --> 00:18:33,362
Right now, I'm leaning towards
approaching the person I like.

429
00:18:33,445 --> 00:18:34,446
Then just do that.

430
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:37,366
How do you think
the person you're attracted to feels?

431
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:39,743
- She doesn't seem to be interested.
- Oh, really?

432
00:18:39,827 --> 00:18:40,869
- Not really.
- Oh, no.

433
00:18:42,454 --> 00:18:45,666
Oh, he's been trying to send
her signals with his eyes this whole time.

434
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:48,210
And Su-ji has no idea
that he's talking about her, huh?

435
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:50,462
Oh, my God. It's you, Su-ji!

436
00:18:50,546 --> 00:18:52,005
KIM JAE-SEO
CHOI HYUK-JOON

437
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:54,800
I don't know about Hyun-seo yet, though.

438
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:57,678
I mean, we went on three dates in a row.

439
00:18:57,761 --> 00:19:01,348
I feel like she probably wants
to go on a date with someone else.

440
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:04,184
Well, actually, I…

441
00:19:05,435 --> 00:19:07,980
already did it. I used the Post Office.

442
00:19:08,063 --> 00:19:10,607
- Oh, really? What did you do?
- Uh-huh.

443
00:19:10,691 --> 00:19:11,733
I gifted a tumbler.

444
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:13,694
Oh, they're talking about the Post Office.

445
00:19:13,777 --> 00:19:15,195
Oh…

446
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:19,908
She hasn't actually
mentioned it to me directly.

447
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:23,245
I'm starting to wonder
if maybe she's into someone else.

448
00:19:24,663 --> 00:19:26,165
- I can see that.
- Mmm.

449
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:29,543
And you know how I've…

450
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:32,254
…been feeling kind of groggy and stuff
since this morning.

451
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:36,133
Pretty much everyone else noticed
that something was kinda off.

452
00:19:36,216 --> 00:19:39,261
And they all asked
how I was doing and stuff.

453
00:19:39,803 --> 00:19:43,765
And I kept sniffling and coughing,
but she didn't notice at all. So…

454
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:45,726
- Oh, really?
- And that…

455
00:19:45,809 --> 00:19:47,978
- Oh, yeah. Then that could be a bad sign.
- Uh-huh.

456
00:19:48,061 --> 00:19:50,689
If someone's interested in you,
they'd usually notice right away.

457
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:53,942
And, uh, I guess since she didn't notice,

458
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:57,613
it just makes me wonder
if she's not all that into me.

459
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:00,157
That's what the scissors actually meant.

460
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,992
- They're like a caution sign.
- Oh, really?

461
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:05,204
When it comes to relationships,
I'm very cautious.

462
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:09,791
And now, it kind of feels like
my proverbial scissors are kicking in.

463
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:10,876
For real.

464
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:12,628
So things are going well,

465
00:20:12,711 --> 00:20:14,713
but alarm bells are going off
for no real reason.

466
00:20:14,796 --> 00:20:17,466
Right. And my guard is up,
because I don't want to get hurt.

467
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:18,467
Mm-hmm.

468
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:21,762
Uh, what's it called? A defense mechanism?

469
00:20:21,845 --> 00:20:24,681
Yeah. Well, it feels like
it's telling me to stop.

470
00:20:25,766 --> 00:20:27,851
I just don't know what to think.

471
00:20:28,977 --> 00:20:31,480
So there's just been
this buildup of hurt feelings.

472
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:32,689
For sure, yes.

473
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:35,984
Yeah, I noticed this about Hyuk-joon
in our early conversations.

474
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:38,403
- He rushes into things. He's impatient.
- Well…

475
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:40,155
- Too impatient.
- You're right.

476
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:43,283
When we last saw Hyun-seo,
she couldn't even look him in the eye.

477
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:45,035
I know. He makes her heart pound.

478
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:48,413
She's nervous around him because now
she has developed an attraction to him.

479
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:49,331
You're right.

480
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:53,543
But Hyuk-joon seems to be mistaking her
nerves and hesitation for indifference.

481
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:54,920
That seems to be the case.

482
00:20:55,003 --> 00:20:56,296
ETERNAL SINGLES' POST OFFICE

483
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:57,923
The light's on. Is someone in there?

484
00:20:58,006 --> 00:20:59,466
Oh, duh, they're always on.

485
00:21:00,842 --> 00:21:02,219
- After you.
- Huh?

486
00:21:03,178 --> 00:21:04,263
Oh, are you guys talking?

487
00:21:04,346 --> 00:21:06,223
- Uh…
- What's this? Huh?

488
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:08,392
- Bye.
- Um, Jae-seo and Hyun-seo?

489
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:11,770
- Maybe now's not the best time.
- I never imagined those two…

490
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:15,857
Oh, wait, do you think they're talking
because he's Hyuk-joon's roommate?

491
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:18,068
- Do you think?
- I think that could be it.

492
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:20,737
It's not like they're confessing
hidden feelings for each other.

493
00:21:20,821 --> 00:21:23,323
Everyone is so sure
there's nothing going on between them.

494
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:25,534
It's probably something about Hyuk-joon.

495
00:21:26,326 --> 00:21:27,703
- Who's this about?
- We're doing this?

496
00:21:27,786 --> 00:21:28,954
- Sharing secrets--
- Let's do it.

497
00:21:30,872 --> 00:21:32,416
- Seo-yoon?
- Yep.

498
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:36,003
- Interesting…
- Aren't you gonna tell me?

499
00:21:36,086 --> 00:21:38,380
Oh, for me, it's…

500
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:42,301
- Him? Gotcha.
- Hyuk-joon.

501
00:21:42,884 --> 00:21:43,969
Hey, listen…

502
00:21:44,928 --> 00:21:47,639
Did Hyuk-joon, um,
ever mention giving a gift to someone?

503
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:49,182
The tumbler?

504
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:53,437
To me? Oh, okay, so it was Hyuk-joon.

505
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:57,065
Oh, man. That kind of makes me nervous.

506
00:21:57,149 --> 00:21:59,151
I mean, we're only three days in.

507
00:21:59,234 --> 00:22:01,778
What if he finds out
everything about me too early?

508
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:02,863
Fair point.

509
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:05,615
That might mean things get too boring
for him later on.

510
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:06,575
Oh, yeah.

511
00:22:06,658 --> 00:22:09,745
And then he might want to stop
learning new things about me.

512
00:22:09,828 --> 00:22:12,706
So I thought I'd try being more strategic,
you know?

513
00:22:12,789 --> 00:22:14,333
Like, kind of… playing hard to get.

514
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:15,459
Ah, so he doesn't know.

515
00:22:15,542 --> 00:22:17,669
So when he asked me today
if I'd been to the Post Office,

516
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:20,297
I said, "No, I haven't.
I don't know anything about it."

517
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:23,216
I really wish she wouldn't play
these weird games.

518
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:26,803
I know, right? Our cast of eternal singles
don't open their hearts very easily,

519
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:29,139
even when they are confronted
with expressions of love directly.

520
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:30,057
Mm-hmm.

521
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:32,601
So ultimately, I think "hard to get"
may have been the wrong call.

522
00:22:32,684 --> 00:22:34,728
Absolutely. That romance
has officially been derailed.

523
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:35,645
You're right.

524
00:22:35,729 --> 00:22:37,522
Well, you've told me a lot,

525
00:22:37,606 --> 00:22:39,649
so it's only fair
that I tell you something now.

526
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:42,903
- Seo-yoon still hasn't made up her mind.
- Right.

527
00:22:43,528 --> 00:22:45,947
Okay, but this is my problem.

528
00:22:46,031 --> 00:22:48,575
I want to make sure
I don't come on too strong.

529
00:22:48,658 --> 00:22:50,619
I don't want her to feel pressured.

530
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:53,538
Maybe you could try writing her a letter.

531
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:57,000
The way things stand right now,
that'd probably work against me.

532
00:22:57,084 --> 00:22:58,418
Hmm…

533
00:22:59,586 --> 00:23:02,464
I really want to be thoughtful
in my approach,

534
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:05,592
so I went to
the Eternal Singles' Post Office today

535
00:23:05,675 --> 00:23:07,010
to gather some information.

536
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:08,929
She seems to like snacks and stuff,

537
00:23:09,012 --> 00:23:10,555
so I think that's a good…

538
00:23:11,181 --> 00:23:12,349
a good starting point.

539
00:23:12,432 --> 00:23:16,728
But, uh, I'm worried that she might feel
like I'm pressuring her,

540
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:19,189
so I'm wondering
if it's too soon for all this.

541
00:23:19,272 --> 00:23:21,358
- Surely snacks are fine.
- Snacks sound okay.

542
00:23:22,275 --> 00:23:24,194
<i>Search by song title.</i>

543
00:23:24,277 --> 00:23:25,487
The Noraebang?

544
00:23:25,570 --> 00:23:29,282
I'll sing one song, and then that's it.
I'll never come back.

545
00:23:29,366 --> 00:23:30,617
Are they going to sing?

546
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,327
- I'm just--
- Did you sing earlier?

547
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:34,454
- It's my first time.
- I need to hear this.

548
00:23:34,538 --> 00:23:37,040
- How about this one?
- "Love… that Bastard"?

549
00:23:37,124 --> 00:23:39,334
She said, "Love… that Bastard"?
With a question mark.

550
00:23:39,418 --> 00:23:41,169
- Okay, you asked for this.
- Oh, my goodness.

551
00:23:42,003 --> 00:23:44,131
Oh, no. Wrong vibe.
This is the wrong vibe.

552
00:23:50,887 --> 00:23:51,972
<i>Uh-huh </i>

553
00:23:53,056 --> 00:23:55,600
I'M ALWAYS IN LOVE ALONE
AND I ALWAYS END UP ALONE

554
00:23:55,684 --> 00:23:58,395
Oh, no. It's already so sad.

555
00:23:58,478 --> 00:24:00,730
<i>And I always end up alone </i>

556
00:24:00,814 --> 00:24:02,983
Oh, God. I can't watch.

557
00:24:03,066 --> 00:24:08,363
<i>I look back alone And I fall apart alone</i>

558
00:24:09,072 --> 00:24:10,407
Come on, Kim Jae-seo!

559
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:13,618
<i>Love, that bastard </i>

560
00:24:13,702 --> 00:24:17,581
<i>When faced with that bastard </i>

561
00:24:18,123 --> 00:24:22,002
<i>I'm always left with nothing </i>

562
00:24:22,085 --> 00:24:25,130
Don't you think snacks
might have been the better option?

563
00:24:25,213 --> 00:24:28,216
<i>I love you </i>

564
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,594
<i>I'm in love with you </i>

565
00:24:31,970 --> 00:24:37,642
<i>A melody no one answers back to </i>

566
00:24:37,726 --> 00:24:40,145
Use the 5 Minute Library already!

567
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:47,360
<i>Even if I can't see straight </i>

568
00:24:47,444 --> 00:24:53,783
<i>I keep ending up</i>
<i>Back in the same place </i>

569
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:57,746
<i>I love you </i>

570
00:24:58,371 --> 00:25:01,374
<i>I love you again </i>

571
00:25:02,334 --> 00:25:04,461
<i>Love comes whenever it wants </i>

572
00:25:04,544 --> 00:25:06,046
Oh, no. Who edited this?

573
00:25:06,129 --> 00:25:08,840
- Wow, this is hysterical.
- Hey, man, you gotta chill.

574
00:25:08,924 --> 00:25:13,053
<i>Whenever it wants </i>

575
00:25:13,136 --> 00:25:17,766
<i>Just as when it came </i>

576
00:25:17,849 --> 00:25:23,396
<i>It leaves without a word </i>

577
00:25:24,981 --> 00:25:27,442
That was like
one of those old music videos.

578
00:25:27,526 --> 00:25:29,861
Or like Im Chang-jung's,
"A Glass of Soju" video!

579
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:32,822
So many flashbacks to how I used to be.
Thanks a lot, Jae-seo.

580
00:25:32,906 --> 00:25:35,200
But still, I'm sure that took
a lot of courage from him.

581
00:25:35,283 --> 00:25:37,702
- He basically professed his love.
- I mean, really, Jae-seo was like…

582
00:25:38,578 --> 00:25:40,956
"I'm getting my feelings
across to her right now."

583
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:43,833
- He was immersed in how cool he looked.
- Totally immersed.

584
00:25:43,917 --> 00:25:47,128
And he's probably thinking it was framed
as this epic moment for the show,

585
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:49,339
and that his feelings
are totally coming across.

586
00:25:50,507 --> 00:25:51,633
Oh, God.

587
00:25:51,716 --> 00:25:55,220
I mean, he sang well and everything, but…

588
00:25:55,303 --> 00:25:57,806
- I mean, come on.
- I don't get it, I simply don't.

589
00:25:57,889 --> 00:25:59,432
- I don't understand why.
- But I--

590
00:25:59,516 --> 00:26:01,810
If anyone can figure it out,
leave a comment.

591
00:26:03,144 --> 00:26:04,354
I'm going to run away.

592
00:26:04,437 --> 00:26:06,523
Oh, come on. She's bailing. She's not…

593
00:26:06,606 --> 00:26:08,525
- You tell me to sing, I run away.
- That's not fair.

594
00:26:08,608 --> 00:26:12,195
Why do I keep making deals
that only I honor? Seriously.

595
00:26:12,279 --> 00:26:14,322
Oh, that was delightful.

596
00:26:14,406 --> 00:26:16,783
- Yeah, but he was actually good.
- She's really leaving.

597
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,869
Jae-seo, that was great.

598
00:26:30,964 --> 00:26:33,967
CHOI HYUN-SEO
LEE HAN-JU

599
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:49,691
So I'd been keeping
the tumbler hidden in my room.

600
00:26:49,774 --> 00:26:53,403
But then I realized that
I needed to think more strategically.

601
00:26:54,112 --> 00:26:58,575
So, since Hyuk-joon is definitely
the one I'm the most attracted to,

602
00:26:59,618 --> 00:27:01,453
I focused my strategies there.

603
00:27:11,546 --> 00:27:13,381
I decided to bring the tumbler with me.

604
00:27:13,465 --> 00:27:14,674
That's it.

605
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:20,221
- I guess she received the tumbler.
- She's got the tumbler.

606
00:27:21,556 --> 00:27:22,932
Oh, my…

607
00:27:24,100 --> 00:27:25,602
She's really showing it off.

608
00:27:26,603 --> 00:27:29,147
- Everyone's looking at it.
- No, I'm good, thanks.

609
00:27:30,065 --> 00:27:32,734
- You got a shout-out.
- Who wants coffee?

610
00:27:33,526 --> 00:27:35,236
Oh, it's just right in front of her.

611
00:27:35,737 --> 00:27:38,114
- You're all here.
- Oh, hello.

612
00:27:38,198 --> 00:27:39,824
Hyuk-joon. He'll definitely see it now.

613
00:27:40,533 --> 00:27:43,036
I took it outside
and drank coffee with it.

614
00:27:45,163 --> 00:27:46,414
But he didn't seem to notice.

615
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:48,166
What?

616
00:27:48,667 --> 00:27:50,752
Uh-oh, are his scissors back?

617
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:52,962
- Did he cut her off?
- Hyuk-joon is miffed right now.

618
00:27:53,046 --> 00:27:54,089
Oh that's it.

619
00:27:54,172 --> 00:27:56,633
He's not being discrete about it.
We get it, you're miffed.

620
00:27:56,716 --> 00:27:58,343
It's one thing
to tell someone they hurt you,

621
00:27:58,426 --> 00:28:00,345
but this attitude implies
you're genuinely miffed.

622
00:28:00,428 --> 00:28:01,262
Mmm.

623
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:03,848
It was fine, but it always ends.

624
00:28:04,516 --> 00:28:07,268
Hey, was that pumpkin
over there yesterday?

625
00:28:07,352 --> 00:28:09,521
Oh, wow. What's with the giant pumpkin?

626
00:28:09,604 --> 00:28:11,690
- There are so many.
- Wait, what's that?

627
00:28:11,773 --> 00:28:14,234
- Are those pumpkins too?
- Is it Halloween today?

628
00:28:14,818 --> 00:28:16,986
- Oh, paper cups. Oh, geez.
- Oh, my.

629
00:28:17,070 --> 00:28:18,655
It's here.

630
00:28:18,738 --> 00:28:21,616
- What could it be? Oh, "The 5 Minute"…
- "New releases"?

631
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:23,201
Wait. New releases? That means new--

632
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:24,369
New information.

633
00:28:24,452 --> 00:28:26,371
Oh, I'm dying to find out.

634
00:28:26,955 --> 00:28:30,834
NEW RELEASES IN STOCK
AT THE 5 MINUTE LIBRARY

635
00:28:30,917 --> 00:28:34,045
I haven't been
to the 5 Minute Library yet,

636
00:28:34,129 --> 00:28:39,008
but just hearing about the new releases
kind of piqued my curiosity.

637
00:28:39,092 --> 00:28:41,845
The new releases won't contain
anything we wrote personally,

638
00:28:41,928 --> 00:28:45,098
so I was really curious
to see what they said.

639
00:28:45,181 --> 00:28:47,475
- Oh, "The 5 Minute"…
- "New releases"?

640
00:28:47,559 --> 00:28:49,519
ONLY THE FIRST 2 PEOPLE TO FIND
KEYS WILL BE ALLOWED TO ENTER

641
00:28:49,602 --> 00:28:52,355
- "Library keys are under the pumpkins."
- That's why there are so many.

642
00:28:52,439 --> 00:28:53,565
- Oh, man.
- Oh, the keys.

643
00:28:57,026 --> 00:28:58,027
- Wait.
- Move, move.

644
00:28:58,111 --> 00:29:00,530
You mean they actually hid the keys
under the pumpkins?

645
00:29:00,613 --> 00:29:01,990
It's like a treasure hunt.

646
00:29:03,658 --> 00:29:05,702
Hey, someone get across the water.

647
00:29:05,785 --> 00:29:07,537
How are we supposed to cross that?

648
00:29:07,620 --> 00:29:09,456
Move, move, move.

649
00:29:09,539 --> 00:29:11,166
- Nothing here.
- Oh, God.

650
00:29:11,249 --> 00:29:14,711
Wow, lots of initiative
from our female eternal singles.

651
00:29:14,794 --> 00:29:17,547
- Couldn't you just give it to me, Jin-woo?
- It's not here, though.

652
00:29:17,630 --> 00:29:18,965
You go find it, Seo-yoon!

653
00:29:19,048 --> 00:29:20,425
Oh, no…

654
00:29:20,508 --> 00:29:22,218
It's not here, it's not here.

655
00:29:24,679 --> 00:29:26,181
Yes! I love it, Su-ji.

656
00:29:26,264 --> 00:29:28,641
I mean, we talked here this morning.

657
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:30,268
It's not here.

658
00:29:30,852 --> 00:29:32,353
Su-ji is the coolest.

659
00:29:33,271 --> 00:29:36,566
Oh, I had to find it.
I had to come in first place again.

660
00:29:36,649 --> 00:29:39,944
Only a few of us could get in,
and I wanted it to be me.

661
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:47,118
I got the impression
that the diaries would be worthless

662
00:29:47,202 --> 00:29:48,703
if it was too late in the game.

663
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:49,746
So it's about time.

664
00:29:49,829 --> 00:29:52,665
Information only really helps you
in the beginning.

665
00:29:52,749 --> 00:29:54,542
The value decreases every day.

666
00:29:54,626 --> 00:29:56,836
I guess the guys are feeling
the time pressure now too.

667
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:58,421
- I know.
- Of course.

668
00:29:58,505 --> 00:30:00,965
- No one's found anything.
- Look for the most natural-looking ones?

669
00:30:03,676 --> 00:30:05,136
It's not here.

670
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:06,679
Out of my way!

671
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:08,389
Move, move, move!

672
00:30:13,603 --> 00:30:15,605
I was running around like crazy,

673
00:30:15,688 --> 00:30:17,941
like, "I have to get in there,
no matter what."

674
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:19,025
I was locked in.

675
00:30:25,031 --> 00:30:26,658
HYUN-SEO OBTAINS THE KEY
TO THE 5 MINUTE LIBRARY

676
00:30:26,741 --> 00:30:28,451
Oh! Hyun-seo found the first one.

677
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:31,663
I found a key.

678
00:30:32,539 --> 00:30:33,540
Nothing yet?

679
00:30:33,623 --> 00:30:35,208
Oh, you got one?

680
00:30:35,291 --> 00:30:36,876
- What?
- No way.

681
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,711
- What? You found one?
- There's one.

682
00:30:38,795 --> 00:30:39,963
- You found one?
- Wow.

683
00:30:40,046 --> 00:30:41,965
- Where was it?
- There's only one left now.

684
00:30:42,549 --> 00:30:43,925
I don't know, I don't know.

685
00:30:44,509 --> 00:30:45,718
Where is it?

686
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:50,181
Oh!

687
00:30:53,226 --> 00:30:54,519
SEUNG-HYUN OBTAINS A KEY

688
00:30:54,602 --> 00:30:56,271
- Oh, I found it.
- He found one.

689
00:30:56,354 --> 00:31:00,066
You know, sometimes I feel like
Seung-hyun really got the devil's luck.

690
00:31:00,149 --> 00:31:03,027
I got lucky
and managed to find one of the two keys.

691
00:31:03,111 --> 00:31:04,654
It was totally by chance.

692
00:31:04,737 --> 00:31:07,282
I can't believe I'm lucky enough
to have found one.

693
00:31:08,074 --> 00:31:09,075
I'm so stoked.

694
00:31:09,158 --> 00:31:13,246
I mean, I just happened to notice
a green pumpkin, and I lifted it up.

695
00:31:13,329 --> 00:31:14,581
There it was.

696
00:31:14,664 --> 00:31:17,584
5 MINUTE LIBRARY

697
00:31:18,835 --> 00:31:20,461
Will she read Hyuk-joon's?

698
00:31:28,011 --> 00:31:29,178
I only get to choose one.

699
00:31:29,262 --> 00:31:31,014
- Just one?
- She only gets to look at one?

700
00:31:31,097 --> 00:31:32,974
- Why are you choosing? Huh?
- Oh, one person.

701
00:31:34,017 --> 00:31:38,646
I originally wanted to look
at Hyuk-joon's and Seung-hyun's diaries.

702
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:40,523
Time's ticking.

703
00:31:44,402 --> 00:31:45,361
Only one.

704
00:31:47,196 --> 00:31:48,197
AHN SEUNG-HYUN

705
00:31:48,281 --> 00:31:49,699
Oh.

706
00:31:49,782 --> 00:31:52,201
Whoa, so she also had feelings
for Seung-hyun.

707
00:31:52,285 --> 00:31:56,372
Is this what Hyun-seo means
when she says she's playing hard to get?

708
00:31:56,456 --> 00:31:58,875
Wait. That's her playing hard to get?

709
00:31:59,792 --> 00:32:02,211
Since I read Hyuk-joon's diary yesterday,

710
00:32:02,295 --> 00:32:03,713
today, I read Seung-hyun's.

711
00:32:03,796 --> 00:32:06,007
But it's a new release,
there might be something new.

712
00:32:06,090 --> 00:32:09,344
Well, I wanted to check
for his ideal type,

713
00:32:09,427 --> 00:32:12,722
like what he would want
for her to look like.

714
00:32:12,805 --> 00:32:15,683
And to check the new release.

715
00:32:16,684 --> 00:32:18,227
But what's in the new release?

716
00:32:18,311 --> 00:32:19,437
Oh!

717
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,813
Ah…

718
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:23,191
YOUR TOP FIRST IMPRESSION PICK?
KIM SOO-HYUN

719
00:32:23,274 --> 00:32:25,944
- Oh, stuff like this? I see.
- Oh, it's about the present.

720
00:32:26,653 --> 00:32:28,321
Wait. That's it?

721
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:31,574
BEST ROTATION DATE CONVERSATION?
HAN SU-JI

722
00:32:31,658 --> 00:32:34,077
Hey, now that she's seen this…

723
00:32:34,702 --> 00:32:37,747
It said that he connected
the most with Su-ji.

724
00:32:38,373 --> 00:32:43,044
It really did seem like Seung-hyun
was interested in Su-ji to me.

725
00:32:43,127 --> 00:32:45,922
But when we were talking
during the Rotation Date,

726
00:32:46,005 --> 00:32:50,218
he made it sound as though
he wasn't interested in her at all.

727
00:32:50,301 --> 00:32:51,302
LAST NIGHT

728
00:32:51,386 --> 00:32:53,930
So is your top pick in Sparks House?

729
00:32:56,307 --> 00:32:58,685
I kind of thought it might be Su-ji.

730
00:32:58,768 --> 00:33:01,312
Is that it? Is she your top pick now?

731
00:33:01,396 --> 00:33:03,398
Oh, well, I did like her.

732
00:33:03,481 --> 00:33:05,650
- But…
- So that's not it?

733
00:33:05,733 --> 00:33:06,734
Uh, huh?

734
00:33:07,318 --> 00:33:08,987
No, th-that's not it.

735
00:33:12,115 --> 00:33:17,412
But when I checked the new release,
it said he felt most connected with Su-ji.

736
00:33:17,495 --> 00:33:20,206
So it's like, "Ah, okay.
Then he did like her."

737
00:33:20,289 --> 00:33:23,001
So I guess I was able
to get some closure there.

738
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:35,596
- Wow. Those new releases reveal a lot of…
- Oh, yeah.

739
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:38,725
Exactly. Reading it might make you feel
really good or really bad.

740
00:33:38,808 --> 00:33:40,977
Well, Hyun-seo just said
she was able to get closure.

741
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:42,061
True, true.

742
00:33:42,145 --> 00:33:45,273
So that means Seung-hyun was
at least on her radar to some extent.

743
00:33:45,356 --> 00:33:46,607
That seems to be the case.

744
00:33:46,691 --> 00:33:48,276
And when Seung-hyun looks at Su-ji's,

745
00:33:48,359 --> 00:33:51,279
Su-ji's favorite Rotation Date partner
will be written there.

746
00:33:51,362 --> 00:33:52,864
- That's right.
- Ah…

747
00:33:52,947 --> 00:33:54,824
He'll be able to see who it is.

748
00:34:00,788 --> 00:34:05,585
As of yesterday, Su-ji has
officially moved up to my top pick.

749
00:34:06,169 --> 00:34:10,840
In the 5 Minute Library,
I read the new release of her diary

750
00:34:10,923 --> 00:34:12,800
and the original one too.

751
00:34:12,884 --> 00:34:15,428
Oh, so Seung-hyun
can check Su-ji's feelings?

752
00:34:16,345 --> 00:34:18,056
Yoon Jung-yun for the first impression.

753
00:34:20,850 --> 00:34:22,977
- Jung-yun for the Rotation as well.
- That's right.

754
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:25,730
- Oh, dear.
- Oh, no.

755
00:34:25,813 --> 00:34:29,984
I think, if I'm being honest
with myself, I kind of saw this coming.

756
00:34:33,362 --> 00:34:34,405
I thought I'd be okay,

757
00:34:34,489 --> 00:34:36,866
but I definitely became
more conscious of it.

758
00:34:36,949 --> 00:34:38,785
- And it really got under my skin.
- Of course.

759
00:34:38,868 --> 00:34:41,079
He confessed his feelings to her
yesterday in his own way.

760
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:42,121
That's right.

761
00:34:44,415 --> 00:34:47,126
Seung-hyun's never been
to the 5 Minute Library before.

762
00:34:47,210 --> 00:34:50,296
- No, he hasn't.
- So he goes straight for the main diary.

763
00:34:56,761 --> 00:35:00,014
Out of all the entries,
the, uh, most memorable one

764
00:35:00,098 --> 00:35:02,892
was how she prefers
a more feminine man to a masculine one.

765
00:35:02,975 --> 00:35:07,980
I'd always thought of myself
as a more effeminate man than most,

766
00:35:08,064 --> 00:35:10,817
so I was actually a bit relieved.

767
00:35:10,900 --> 00:35:12,985
- He's right. He's effeminate.
- Oh, he's adorable.

768
00:35:21,702 --> 00:35:24,413
God, it's really a shame
he did that thing with the tangerine hat.

769
00:35:24,497 --> 00:35:26,374
They were vibing, but…

770
00:35:26,457 --> 00:35:29,669
Whose did you read?
Did you check the new release or…

771
00:35:29,752 --> 00:35:32,338
- There was a new release for each person.
- Ah…

772
00:35:32,421 --> 00:35:34,090
Oh, another one for each person.

773
00:35:34,173 --> 00:35:35,174
- Wow…
- Oh, my God.

774
00:35:35,258 --> 00:35:36,300
- That's insane.
- No way.

775
00:35:36,384 --> 00:35:39,053
Tomorrow I'm wearing running shoes.
Seriously.

776
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:41,222
I really want to go in.
Just once, seriously.

777
00:35:41,305 --> 00:35:42,181
Right…

778
00:35:42,265 --> 00:35:44,142
I left early 'cause I had time at the end.

779
00:35:44,225 --> 00:35:47,145
- You checked yesterday.
- Wow, rub it in our faces, why don't you?

780
00:35:47,228 --> 00:35:49,647
- No, I checked someone else's today.
- Oh, okay.

781
00:35:49,730 --> 00:35:51,399
- Yeah, I checked someone else's.
- Oh, really?

782
00:35:51,482 --> 00:35:54,402
Oh, Hyuk-joon couldn't look more sour.

783
00:35:54,485 --> 00:35:56,779
- Why would she say something…
- She's doing it on purpose.

784
00:36:00,032 --> 00:36:01,993
- Grab it. We got something.
- Huh?

785
00:36:03,286 --> 00:36:05,163
"Female singles going on three-way dates."

786
00:36:05,246 --> 00:36:06,956
- Please don't do this.
- Three-way date?

787
00:36:07,039 --> 00:36:08,374
What's a three-way date?

788
00:36:09,709 --> 00:36:12,503
"The female singles will go on a date
with their top and second picks."

789
00:36:12,587 --> 00:36:15,173
The three of them? Wow.

790
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:18,885
They don't know who's the top,
and who's the second pick? Oh!

791
00:36:18,968 --> 00:36:21,387
MALE SINGLES DON'T KNOW WHICH
IS THE TOP PICK OR SECOND PICK

792
00:36:22,054 --> 00:36:24,765
As soon as we got the text,
we all immediately figured out

793
00:36:24,849 --> 00:36:27,977
that we'd be going on a date
with our top and second picks.

794
00:36:28,060 --> 00:36:30,313
We mentioned it
in the interview yesterday, so…

795
00:36:30,396 --> 00:36:34,567
Uh, there was still a lot I hadn't
talked about with my top two picks.

796
00:36:34,650 --> 00:36:36,903
So I wanted to have
a basic conversation with them.

797
00:36:36,986 --> 00:36:39,113
Oh, I think this is great.

798
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:44,577
This is a really good opportunity
to go on a date with both of them.

799
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:49,373
Wait, so the male singles don't know
if they're the number one or two choice?

800
00:36:49,457 --> 00:36:50,333
Right, no idea.

801
00:36:50,416 --> 00:36:53,336
It'll keep them on their toes, especially
if it's a female contestant they like.

802
00:36:53,419 --> 00:36:55,379
- They're setting them up to be rivals.
- Hold up…

803
00:36:55,463 --> 00:36:58,341
- We might have some fights break out.
- They're creating more competition.

804
00:36:58,424 --> 00:37:00,468
There's no way
these guys will get in a fight.

805
00:37:00,551 --> 00:37:02,386
That's true.
They're incapable of fighting.

806
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:05,723
- They're more likely to concede.
- Of course. Way more likely to concede.

807
00:37:05,806 --> 00:37:08,976
And I think this will also make
the female singles really uncomfortable.

808
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:10,269
- Right.
- Totally.

809
00:37:10,353 --> 00:37:12,188
Both guys will be on this date,

810
00:37:12,271 --> 00:37:14,690
knowing they're either
the first or second picks.

811
00:37:14,774 --> 00:37:16,692
- They're being exposed.
- That's just…

812
00:37:16,776 --> 00:37:19,237
Anyway, from the male singles'
point of view,

813
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:22,281
this is an opportunity to find out who's
attracted to them and show off a little.

814
00:37:22,365 --> 00:37:24,742
- This could be a good thing.
- You're right.

815
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:31,082
- Ooh. Great vibes in here.
- Wow.

816
00:37:31,165 --> 00:37:33,709
SU-JI'S THREE-WAY DATE

817
00:37:36,963 --> 00:37:40,925
My top and second picks were the two
who'd left the biggest impression on me

818
00:37:41,008 --> 00:37:43,803
during the Rotation conversations.

819
00:37:44,387 --> 00:37:46,847
So I thought I'd be able
to talk to them a bit more.

820
00:37:49,225 --> 00:37:51,310
- Jung-yun and Seung-hyun?
- I think so.

821
00:37:59,902 --> 00:38:02,280
Hello.

822
00:38:02,363 --> 00:38:03,364
Hi.

823
00:38:03,447 --> 00:38:05,825
- Oh, it's Jung-yun.
- Jung-yun.

824
00:38:05,908 --> 00:38:07,410
JUNG-YUN
SU-JI'S TOP PICK

825
00:38:07,493 --> 00:38:09,203
- Hello. Please take a seat.
- Hello.

826
00:38:09,287 --> 00:38:11,914
- Don't these two look good together?
- They do look good together.

827
00:38:11,998 --> 00:38:13,207
- Hello.
- Hello.

828
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:16,377
- I hope these two start dating.
- They look so great together.

829
00:38:18,629 --> 00:38:22,508
I was really happy
to finally have a chance to talk to her.

830
00:38:23,092 --> 00:38:26,137
- No more "Could you ask to see me?"
- None.

831
00:38:26,220 --> 00:38:28,556
You know, when we had
our ten-minute date yesterday…

832
00:38:28,639 --> 00:38:29,682
Yeah, right, right.

833
00:38:29,765 --> 00:38:32,685
…I thought we might have some time
to talk afterwards.

834
00:38:32,768 --> 00:38:35,604
But then we were told that we had
to go back to our rooms right away…

835
00:38:35,688 --> 00:38:36,605
Oh, same. Yeah.

836
00:38:36,689 --> 00:38:39,150
…so we couldn't continue the conversation.

837
00:38:39,233 --> 00:38:40,109
Uh-huh.

838
00:38:40,693 --> 00:38:43,404
It would be nice to use this opportunity
to talk a little more.

839
00:38:43,487 --> 00:38:45,031
Mmm. I'd like that.

840
00:38:45,114 --> 00:38:47,992
Aw, I'm getting butterflies
watching them being all shy.

841
00:38:48,075 --> 00:38:52,496
I know we talked a little bit yesterday,
but I still have a question for you.

842
00:38:52,580 --> 00:38:54,290
- Oh, really?
- Yeah. So…

843
00:38:54,373 --> 00:38:55,833
- What is it?
- Well…

844
00:38:55,916 --> 00:38:59,295
You gave me the towel,
and then with the metronome,

845
00:38:59,378 --> 00:39:01,839
you picked it thinking it belonged to me.

846
00:39:01,922 --> 00:39:03,007
- Right?
- Right.

847
00:39:03,090 --> 00:39:06,719
- And you picked me in the Library too, so…
- Right.

848
00:39:06,802 --> 00:39:09,347
I kind of…
Well, I keep going around and around--

849
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:11,515
Why are you beating
around the bush so much?

850
00:39:11,599 --> 00:39:14,060
- Just hurry up and say it. Yeah.
- I guess I am… Okay.

851
00:39:14,143 --> 00:39:17,229
Um, I guess I want to know
what you were feeling?

852
00:39:17,313 --> 00:39:20,399
Like, what was your state of mind
when you picked me?

853
00:39:20,483 --> 00:39:21,650
My state of mind?

854
00:39:21,734 --> 00:39:23,527
- Oh, for the love of…
- That's what you ask?

855
00:39:23,611 --> 00:39:24,779
Why are you interviewing her?

856
00:39:24,862 --> 00:39:26,697
So that's the kind of question
we've resorted to.

857
00:39:26,781 --> 00:39:29,450
- This feels like an interview.
- She's already told you everything.

858
00:39:29,533 --> 00:39:31,369
- This is just…
- You know everything.

859
00:39:31,452 --> 00:39:34,038
Should she elaborate?
Does he want her to confess her feelings?

860
00:39:34,121 --> 00:39:35,873
Who do you think you are?

861
00:39:37,166 --> 00:39:38,709
"Who do you think you are?"

862
00:39:38,793 --> 00:39:42,129
Do you want a written report
explaining why she likes you?

863
00:39:42,713 --> 00:39:45,549
- I'm genuinely curious, Jung-yun.
- God, why is this so funny?

864
00:39:45,633 --> 00:39:47,968
Hey, I thought you were gonna be
the supportive guy today.

865
00:39:48,052 --> 00:39:49,845
He couldn't have had an easier setup.

866
00:39:49,929 --> 00:39:51,472
Does she owe you a written explanation?

867
00:39:51,555 --> 00:39:53,933
An opportunity to express his feelings,
but instead…

868
00:39:54,016 --> 00:39:57,812
Should she jump and shout "L-O-V-E"
like a cheerleader?

869
00:39:59,688 --> 00:40:01,065
My state of mind?

870
00:40:04,485 --> 00:40:08,364
Well, since I really did think
you made the best first impression,

871
00:40:08,447 --> 00:40:10,366
I wanted to keep talking to you.

872
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:14,036
But on the first day,
you were so, so quiet.

873
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:15,162
Right.

874
00:40:15,246 --> 00:40:17,957
And then I was disoriented
and trying to get acclimated.

875
00:40:18,040 --> 00:40:20,209
I ended up just kinda sitting there.

876
00:40:20,292 --> 00:40:22,461
So I wanted to talk to you, but…

877
00:40:24,713 --> 00:40:25,631
Who's…

878
00:40:25,714 --> 00:40:27,800
- Is it Seung-hyun?
- I guess.

879
00:40:29,552 --> 00:40:32,179
Oh, hello.

880
00:40:32,263 --> 00:40:35,015
Hello, second arrival. Hello.

881
00:40:36,058 --> 00:40:37,852
Why is he…

882
00:40:41,647 --> 00:40:44,024
What? Hyuk-joon?

883
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:46,527
- Whoa. Wait a second.
- Hyuk-joon, not Seung-hyun?

884
00:40:46,610 --> 00:40:50,614
Wait, why? When?
How did Su-ji pick Hyuk-joon? How?

885
00:40:50,698 --> 00:40:54,535
- Hello.
- Hey, hello. Hey, there.

886
00:40:54,618 --> 00:40:56,078
HYUK-JOON
SU-JI'S SECOND PICK

887
00:40:56,162 --> 00:40:58,706
- Want to take a seat?
- Well, sure, yeah.

888
00:40:58,789 --> 00:41:00,875
- Did you know it was me?
- No, no clue.

889
00:41:01,917 --> 00:41:04,795
- Why is this so funny to me?
- What's funny?

890
00:41:04,879 --> 00:41:07,131
He just always makes me laugh
for some reason.

891
00:41:07,214 --> 00:41:09,633
- Makes you laugh? Dangerous.
- That is dangerous.

892
00:41:09,717 --> 00:41:10,926
The way you say hello…

893
00:41:11,010 --> 00:41:13,387
- Jung-yun doesn't look happy.
- That sour face again.

894
00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:14,972
I was a bit surprised, but…

895
00:41:15,055 --> 00:41:18,267
I personally felt like Hyuk-joon
is a pretty handsome guy,

896
00:41:18,350 --> 00:41:21,395
so I needed to stay
on my guard around him.

897
00:41:22,730 --> 00:41:24,398
…and stuff.

898
00:41:25,274 --> 00:41:29,320
I was honestly shocked because
I thought Su-ji wasn't interested in me.

899
00:41:29,403 --> 00:41:31,780
So I was like, almost in a daze.

900
00:41:31,864 --> 00:41:33,324
This was really unexpected.

901
00:41:37,161 --> 00:41:41,540
I chose him as my second pick
after we had our ten-minute conversation.

902
00:41:41,624 --> 00:41:45,085
When it was just us,
it was like he was a different person.

903
00:41:45,169 --> 00:41:48,756
He was nothing like how I had imagined.
Seriously, just different.

904
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:52,426
Not like the opposite,
but just a little teensy bit different.

905
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:55,387
So were you with them then,
the person you picked?

906
00:41:55,971 --> 00:41:58,098
- Yes.
- Yes? Oh…

907
00:41:58,182 --> 00:42:00,392
- As for who it is, that's a secret.
- I think I know.

908
00:42:00,476 --> 00:42:01,477
- Oh, really?
- Yes, really.

909
00:42:01,560 --> 00:42:03,604
- But I won't say anything.
- You must be pretty clever then.

910
00:42:03,687 --> 00:42:06,565
- Kind of.
- Oh, really? Oh…

911
00:42:07,191 --> 00:42:08,484
I could help you out.

912
00:42:08,567 --> 00:42:11,153
No, you don't have to help me.
You don't have to help me.

913
00:42:11,237 --> 00:42:12,738
- I could help you out.
- Wow, you're so kind.

914
00:42:12,821 --> 00:42:15,658
You seem much more kind than I would
have thought from first impression.

915
00:42:15,741 --> 00:42:16,825
What did you think of me?

916
00:42:16,909 --> 00:42:19,161
When I first met you,
you weren't this suave.

917
00:42:19,245 --> 00:42:23,207
But out of nowhere, you've suddenly
turned into a smooth talker.

918
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:25,709
Overnight smooth talker.

919
00:42:26,418 --> 00:42:28,629
I've never met someone like you,
so it's funny.

920
00:42:28,712 --> 00:42:30,589
- Why is that?
- I just think you're fascinating.

921
00:42:30,673 --> 00:42:32,383
- Interesting. Wow.
- It's a good thing.

922
00:42:32,466 --> 00:42:34,426
I like funny things. They fascinate me.

923
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:36,595
- Oh, really?
- Yeah. You're the bomb. The bomb.

924
00:42:38,973 --> 00:42:42,017
All right! Wow, this is so much fun.

925
00:42:42,101 --> 00:42:44,853
- Oh, I think she felt something.
- Oh, yeah. She got a feeling.

926
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:47,022
Oh, you're really throwing me off.

927
00:42:47,106 --> 00:42:49,149
You're the first person
to throw me off like this.

928
00:42:49,233 --> 00:42:50,818
She's got butterflies.

929
00:42:50,901 --> 00:42:52,069
She's got butterflies.

930
00:42:52,152 --> 00:42:54,488
Hyuk-joon kept throwing these lines at me.

931
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:56,574
He kept me on my toes, you know?

932
00:42:56,657 --> 00:42:57,700
That's why I picked him.

933
00:42:57,783 --> 00:43:01,161
It was a "No one's ever thrown me off
my game like this" kind of thing.

934
00:43:01,245 --> 00:43:04,957
And then Hyuk-joon came in,
and he had on this cologne.

935
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:06,667
I don't normally like perfume,

936
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:09,169
but he sat down,
and I really liked the scent.

937
00:43:09,253 --> 00:43:10,254
Like a lot.

938
00:43:10,337 --> 00:43:13,132
So that was the first point
where I was like, "Oh!"

939
00:43:13,215 --> 00:43:15,259
The way things are going…

940
00:43:15,342 --> 00:43:17,595
- Oh, my God, Su-ji?
- …Jung-yun's totally at risk.

941
00:43:17,678 --> 00:43:19,013
It's the danger zone.

942
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:20,764
Oh, no.

943
00:43:20,848 --> 00:43:22,766
THE MALE SINGLES DON'T KNOW
WHICH IS THE TOP OR SECOND PICK

944
00:43:23,267 --> 00:43:25,728
Day four. How are you guys doing?

945
00:43:26,687 --> 00:43:27,896
Hmm…

946
00:43:27,980 --> 00:43:29,607
- How are things for you?
- Me?

947
00:43:29,690 --> 00:43:31,150
I'm really confused too.

948
00:43:31,233 --> 00:43:33,652
See, I thought there was
a clear delineation

949
00:43:33,736 --> 00:43:37,573
between those I felt I'd be attracted to
and those I wouldn't.

950
00:43:37,656 --> 00:43:39,199
Just a very clear divide.

951
00:43:39,283 --> 00:43:42,870
But yesterday, I got to talk to everyone
for ten minutes each, right?

952
00:43:42,953 --> 00:43:45,789
And it was kind of different
from what I'd imagined.

953
00:43:45,873 --> 00:43:48,459
- She's talking about Hyuk-joon.
- Yeah.

954
00:43:48,542 --> 00:43:50,544
Uh, I think it was the same for me.

955
00:43:50,628 --> 00:43:54,965
At first, I came in thinking
that there's gotta be someone

956
00:43:55,049 --> 00:43:57,134
who's a definitive match for me here.

957
00:43:57,217 --> 00:43:58,719
- Me too.
- Oh, totally.

958
00:43:58,802 --> 00:44:01,472
But then I worried that
maybe I judged too quickly.

959
00:44:01,555 --> 00:44:04,266
- Right…
- I loved listening to everyone talk, and--

960
00:44:04,350 --> 00:44:06,935
- Right?
- Yeah. It made me want to find out more.

961
00:44:07,019 --> 00:44:08,103
- Totally.
- Mm-hmm.

962
00:44:08,187 --> 00:44:12,441
And that's why I thought
I should really open up my mind a bit

963
00:44:12,524 --> 00:44:14,151
and rethink this again.

964
00:44:14,234 --> 00:44:16,320
- Same. I totally thought the same thing.
- Yeah.

965
00:44:16,403 --> 00:44:18,656
- Hmm…
- Mm-hmm…

966
00:44:20,074 --> 00:44:22,785
So did your rankings change a little too?

967
00:44:22,868 --> 00:44:25,579
Anything shift
after yesterday's conversations?

968
00:44:25,663 --> 00:44:27,414
- Hmm…
- For me…

969
00:44:27,498 --> 00:44:29,833
See that? He beat him to the punch again.

970
00:44:30,459 --> 00:44:32,670
I've changed my mind about the Library.

971
00:44:32,753 --> 00:44:33,629
- Mmm.
- Mm-hmm.

972
00:44:33,712 --> 00:44:36,799
So, uh, based on yesterday's conversation,

973
00:44:37,383 --> 00:44:39,885
I feel like I actually
have someone specifically

974
00:44:39,968 --> 00:44:44,473
I want to find out more about
in the 5 Minute Library now

975
00:44:44,556 --> 00:44:46,934
after my ten-minute conversation with her.

976
00:44:47,017 --> 00:44:49,812
Jung-yun sure takes a while
to get his words out sometimes.

977
00:44:49,895 --> 00:44:50,979
Not a single word yet.

978
00:44:51,063 --> 00:44:52,064
This looks bad.

979
00:44:52,147 --> 00:44:54,024
Don't you guys have any questions for me?

980
00:44:54,108 --> 00:44:55,442
Um…

981
00:44:55,526 --> 00:45:00,364
We kind of had a brief chat in the lounge
about our ideal types, right?

982
00:45:00,447 --> 00:45:01,448
Right.

983
00:45:01,532 --> 00:45:04,243
Can we maybe go into
a little more detail about…

984
00:45:05,536 --> 00:45:07,204
- Yeah? Right, okay.
- Exactly.

985
00:45:07,287 --> 00:45:08,706
That kind of thing. I'm curious.

986
00:45:08,789 --> 00:45:10,374
What a conversationalist.

987
00:45:10,457 --> 00:45:13,419
Ideally, we'd have good conversations,
but they'd be exciting,

988
00:45:13,502 --> 00:45:15,671
and sometimes you can feel
a little tension, you know?

989
00:45:15,754 --> 00:45:18,340
- She's talking about Hyuk-joon.
- Everything is about Hyuk-joon.

990
00:45:18,424 --> 00:45:21,760
And it's just not the context
of the conversations.

991
00:45:21,844 --> 00:45:24,555
I kind of pay attention
to the way they speak too.

992
00:45:24,638 --> 00:45:26,432
- Mm-hmm.
- The way they speak?

993
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:27,808
Mm-hmm.

994
00:45:27,891 --> 00:45:29,143
- In what way?
- In what way?

995
00:45:29,226 --> 00:45:30,686
I like someone with a gentle manner.

996
00:45:30,769 --> 00:45:32,521
But if they're like that all the time,

997
00:45:32,604 --> 00:45:34,314
it can get a little frustrating too,
you know?

998
00:45:34,398 --> 00:45:36,817
- Mm-hmm.
- I don't think I like that.

999
00:45:36,900 --> 00:45:38,402
- Oh…
- That's Jung-yun.

1000
00:45:38,485 --> 00:45:39,945
Gentle, but direct?

1001
00:45:40,028 --> 00:45:43,824
I want them to be clear.
I want them to be clear when they talk.

1002
00:45:43,907 --> 00:45:44,742
Mm-hmm.

1003
00:45:44,825 --> 00:45:47,703
Because if they keep saying things
in a roundabout way,

1004
00:45:47,786 --> 00:45:49,413
I sometimes don't get what they're saying.

1005
00:45:49,496 --> 00:45:50,664
Yeah, that kind of thing.

1006
00:45:50,748 --> 00:45:53,834
Su-ji, girl! We're just trashing him
right to his face? To his face?

1007
00:45:53,917 --> 00:45:57,212
That one felt like a personal jab.

1008
00:45:57,296 --> 00:46:01,592
I think I gave her a long answer
in our previous conversation.

1009
00:46:01,675 --> 00:46:05,804
And that comment felt
like it was pretty pointed, so…

1010
00:46:06,513 --> 00:46:10,184
I feel the same way.
A person's delivery really matters to me.

1011
00:46:10,267 --> 00:46:13,312
And I also don't like it
when people beat around the bush.

1012
00:46:13,395 --> 00:46:17,775
I'm more comfortable with people
who are clear about yes or no.

1013
00:46:17,858 --> 00:46:23,197
And, uh, those are the ones I'm much more
interested in getting to know better.

1014
00:46:23,280 --> 00:46:25,199
- Yeah, I think we're similar.
- Mm-hmm.

1015
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:28,660
Say something, my guy, please!
You gotta do it!

1016
00:46:29,453 --> 00:46:32,664
Me, I've been really curious
to know what you like.

1017
00:46:32,748 --> 00:46:35,250
Hmm, give me a category,
and I'll tell you everything.

1018
00:46:35,334 --> 00:46:36,627
- Uh, hobbies.
- Hobbies?

1019
00:46:36,710 --> 00:46:40,088
- Mm-hmm.
- Ah, for hobbies, I absolutely love anime.

1020
00:46:40,672 --> 00:46:43,550
- Hyuk-joon does too.
- My favorite show is <i>Hunter X Hunter</i>.

1021
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:46,053
I also like tennis and hiking.

1022
00:46:46,136 --> 00:46:48,639
I've been to Seoraksan.
I stayed the night there.

1023
00:46:48,722 --> 00:46:50,140
- Oh, okay.
- It was fun.

1024
00:46:51,016 --> 00:46:53,435
You know, this is kind of
a weird coincidence, but…

1025
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:56,313
my hobby is hiking.

1026
00:46:56,396 --> 00:46:57,439


1027
00:46:57,523 --> 00:46:59,775
- Don't lie to me. Seriously.
- No, seriously.

1028
00:46:59,858 --> 00:47:02,152
I climb Hallasan without taking
a single break to the top.

1029
00:47:02,236 --> 00:47:04,905
- Really?
- Hyuk-joon is gonna feel the call of fate.

1030
00:47:04,988 --> 00:47:07,825
- I seriously think I'm a great hiker.
- Really?

1031
00:47:07,908 --> 00:47:10,911
Uh-huh. So wherever I go with my friends,
they always beg me to please wait up.

1032
00:47:10,994 --> 00:47:12,538
- Oh, to slow down?
- Seriously.

1033
00:47:12,621 --> 00:47:14,164
I even brought a pair of KEENs here.

1034
00:47:14,248 --> 00:47:15,374
- You know, the shoes.
- Oh!

1035
00:47:16,416 --> 00:47:18,001
Uh-huh. So even for this trip,

1036
00:47:18,085 --> 00:47:21,463
I figured since I'm visiting Jeju Island,
I should visit an <i>oreum </i>at least once.

1037
00:47:21,547 --> 00:47:24,258
The thing is,
I also brought my workout clothes

1038
00:47:24,341 --> 00:47:26,176
because I figured I'd go hiking.

1039
00:47:26,260 --> 00:47:27,845
- Just in case.
- Oh, really?

1040
00:47:27,928 --> 00:47:29,388
Oh, my. He threw hobbies out there

1041
00:47:29,471 --> 00:47:31,890
and ended up losing control
of the conversation again.

1042
00:47:31,974 --> 00:47:34,685
- That's really interesting.
- I gotta admit, it is.

1043
00:47:34,768 --> 00:47:36,436
- It's not a very common hobby.
- I know, right?

1044
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:38,856
- Right.
- If I'm being honest, I wrote "ocean."

1045
00:47:38,939 --> 00:47:40,399
No, say mountain! Quick!

1046
00:47:40,482 --> 00:47:41,775
- Really?
- Oh, really?

1047
00:47:41,859 --> 00:47:44,820
- I guess most people do choose the ocean.
- Oh, yeah.

1048
00:47:44,903 --> 00:47:49,366
I just love sitting
and looking out at the wide-open horizon.

1049
00:47:49,449 --> 00:47:51,618
- Then you must be loving this.
- Lord…

1050
00:47:52,244 --> 00:47:53,453
Mm-hmm.

1051
00:47:54,746 --> 00:47:57,916
Hmm, well, that's a new revelation.

1052
00:47:58,000 --> 00:47:59,793
I'm so surprised.

1053
00:48:00,586 --> 00:48:03,213
I know, right? Seriously,
I think it's such a weird coincidence.

1054
00:48:03,297 --> 00:48:04,464
Me too.

1055
00:48:04,548 --> 00:48:07,009
Our hobbies matched better than I thought.

1056
00:48:07,593 --> 00:48:11,221
So at first, I thought
we wouldn't be at all compatible.

1057
00:48:11,305 --> 00:48:15,767
But I was curious to learn more about her.
And I wanted to talk to her more.

1058
00:48:15,851 --> 00:48:18,353
Of course,
since they share a lot in common.

1059
00:48:18,437 --> 00:48:21,857
During the date, Hyuk-joon took the lead

1060
00:48:21,940 --> 00:48:26,403
and asked more questions
and whatnot than I did,

1061
00:48:26,486 --> 00:48:28,822
which made me feel a bit uneasy.

1062
00:48:28,906 --> 00:48:33,619
But after the conversation,
uh, it gave me a lot to think about.

1063
00:48:34,369 --> 00:48:38,165
First of all, I think it's safe to say
that I lack courage,

1064
00:48:38,248 --> 00:48:42,169
which is why I've made up my mind
to change myself.

1065
00:48:42,252 --> 00:48:47,549
So, um, I'm going to make it a point
to be a little braver going forward.

1066
00:48:49,134 --> 00:48:51,053
The topic of hiking came up,

1067
00:48:51,136 --> 00:48:53,805
and Hyuk-joon suddenly said
that he liked hiking,

1068
00:48:53,889 --> 00:48:56,850
so we started talking
about why he liked it.

1069
00:48:56,934 --> 00:49:00,103
Since Jung-yun doesn't
have much hiking experience,

1070
00:49:00,187 --> 00:49:02,522
I had more to talk about with Hyuk-joon.

1071
00:49:02,606 --> 00:49:05,359
It's not like I wanted
to talk to one person more,

1072
00:49:05,442 --> 00:49:07,527
and didn't want to talk to the other.

1073
00:49:07,611 --> 00:49:10,197
I just think I need
to talk to both of them.

1074
00:49:11,698 --> 00:49:13,867
Still, my top pick remains the same.

1075
00:49:13,951 --> 00:49:17,454
Jung-yun is my top pick,
and Hyuk-joon is my second pick.

1076
00:49:19,164 --> 00:49:20,958
But Su-ji did take a jab at him.

1077
00:49:21,041 --> 00:49:23,502
- Jung-yun needs to adjust to her feedback.
- That's true.

1078
00:49:23,585 --> 00:49:25,963
- Her way of saying, "Don't do that again."
- Right.

1079
00:49:26,046 --> 00:49:28,882
But she wouldn't have even bothered
taking a jab at Jung-yun

1080
00:49:28,966 --> 00:49:30,467
if she weren't interested in him.

1081
00:49:30,550 --> 00:49:32,344
That was deliberately directed at him.

1082
00:49:32,427 --> 00:49:35,722
But that scene felt like something
straight out of a TV drama for me.

1083
00:49:35,806 --> 00:49:39,267
There's always some third party trying
to muscle their way into a relationship.

1084
00:49:39,351 --> 00:49:42,145
You think there's some huge crisis,
but it all works out in the end.

1085
00:49:42,229 --> 00:49:44,314
- Right, right.
- That's what this felt like.

1086
00:49:44,398 --> 00:49:46,191
'Cause the male lead
comes to a realization and…

1087
00:49:48,902 --> 00:49:51,071
- Wow.
- What is this place?

1088
00:49:54,241 --> 00:49:57,077
- Oh, it's the singing bowls.
- Oh, wow.

1089
00:49:57,160 --> 00:49:59,663
- What a nice relaxing space.
- It's therapy.

1090
00:49:59,746 --> 00:50:01,581
SINGING BOWL
MEDITATION EXPERIENCE

1091
00:50:02,207 --> 00:50:04,292
SOO-HYUN'S THREE-WAY DATE

1092
00:50:04,376 --> 00:50:05,585
- Wow.
- Wow.

1093
00:50:07,212 --> 00:50:09,381
There's great comedic potential here.

1094
00:50:13,010 --> 00:50:14,553
What is this?

1095
00:50:14,636 --> 00:50:18,348
- Uh… What the…
- It's like that scene from <i>The Wailing</i>.

1096
00:50:20,976 --> 00:50:23,645
- How does one have a date here?
- I know, right?

1097
00:50:24,146 --> 00:50:25,313
This was pretty nice.

1098
00:50:25,397 --> 00:50:27,899
I really felt like I could lay here
and get my thoughts in order.

1099
00:50:27,983 --> 00:50:29,276
Just so relaxing.

1100
00:50:34,281 --> 00:50:36,450
I wonder who Soo-hyun's picked.

1101
00:50:37,451 --> 00:50:38,994
- Lee Jin-woo.
- Jin-woo.

1102
00:50:39,077 --> 00:50:41,079
JIN-WOO
SOO-HYUN'S TOP PICK

1103
00:50:46,585 --> 00:50:48,712
I bet that caught him off guard.

1104
00:50:48,795 --> 00:50:50,380
That's just…

1105
00:50:54,843 --> 00:50:56,470
He's just stepping around her?

1106
00:51:02,142 --> 00:51:03,810
He should at least say hi.

1107
00:51:03,894 --> 00:51:05,020
Uh, why isn't he saying hi?

1108
00:51:05,103 --> 00:51:09,107
Actually, it's rather difficult
to get the timing right to say anything.

1109
00:51:11,443 --> 00:51:13,862
As you can see,
it's constantly ringing right now.

1110
00:51:13,945 --> 00:51:17,074
It's hard to strike up a conversation
when you don't want to interrupt.

1111
00:51:22,120 --> 00:51:24,748
- She's too immersed right now.
- I mean…

1112
00:51:33,924 --> 00:51:34,925
Oh, who is it?

1113
00:51:36,885 --> 00:51:38,512
- Seung-hyun.
- I see…

1114
00:51:38,595 --> 00:51:40,388
Why is he dressed like a Buddhist monk?

1115
00:51:40,472 --> 00:51:41,807
"Buddhist Monk."

1116
00:51:43,100 --> 00:51:46,019
- Oh, wow, he really…
- Oh, it's here, it's here. Come in.

1117
00:51:46,103 --> 00:51:47,813
- Oh, come on. It's over here.
- Come on, guys.

1118
00:51:47,896 --> 00:51:49,356
That's the place, that's the place.

1119
00:51:54,903 --> 00:51:56,071
What are you gonna do?

1120
00:51:56,154 --> 00:51:58,448
- They're all lying down.
- What are you gonna do?

1121
00:51:58,532 --> 00:52:01,409
I went in there,
and the two of them were just lying there.

1122
00:52:01,493 --> 00:52:03,286
So I was like, "Wh-What is going on here?"

1123
00:52:03,370 --> 00:52:06,123
Okay, please lie down comfortably.

1124
00:52:08,792 --> 00:52:10,252
Has Soo-hyun fallen asleep?

1125
00:52:10,335 --> 00:52:12,129
- Soo-hyun's in deep sleep.
- Oh, geez.

1126
00:52:12,212 --> 00:52:14,881
She probably doesn't even care
who comes or goes at this point.

1127
00:52:23,056 --> 00:52:25,142
He didn't even unfold the blanket.

1128
00:52:26,935 --> 00:52:30,981
Okay, now, please roll
onto your left side.

1129
00:52:32,065 --> 00:52:34,985
From your current position,
roll onto your left side.

1130
00:52:35,068 --> 00:52:38,155
Look at that.
Soo-hyun isn't even opening her eyes.

1131
00:52:42,325 --> 00:52:46,454
Okay.
Keeping your eyes closed, please sit up.

1132
00:52:47,455 --> 00:52:50,417
Please sit facing this direction.

1133
00:52:54,713 --> 00:52:57,382
- Soo-hyun. Seung-hyun, why are you…
- Open your eyes, sheesh.

1134
00:52:57,966 --> 00:53:01,219
Press the palms of your hands
together in front of your chest.

1135
00:53:05,432 --> 00:53:08,310
Did you see that? He did this because
he couldn't press his palms together.

1136
00:53:09,769 --> 00:53:12,981
Now, use your palms
to cover each of your eyes.

1137
00:53:16,234 --> 00:53:18,862
Now, slowly open both eyes.

1138
00:53:19,654 --> 00:53:21,656
Now they've confirmed
each other's presence.

1139
00:53:21,740 --> 00:53:23,491
- Please sit comfortably.
- When did you get here?

1140
00:53:23,575 --> 00:53:26,036
- These are hand warmers.
- She had no idea.

1141
00:53:26,119 --> 00:53:27,120
Oh.

1142
00:53:27,204 --> 00:53:29,998
Right.

1143
00:53:32,918 --> 00:53:35,337
I mean, I got up,
and the two of you were both…

1144
00:53:35,420 --> 00:53:37,464
She opened her eyes to her top two picks.

1145
00:53:37,547 --> 00:53:40,300
- So you got here while I was laying down?
- Uh-huh.

1146
00:53:40,383 --> 00:53:43,470
I came in,
and you two were just lying there.

1147
00:53:43,553 --> 00:53:44,846
Wait, then you arrived together?

1148
00:53:44,930 --> 00:53:46,556
Oh, no, no. We came separately.

1149
00:53:46,640 --> 00:53:48,183
- I was the second to arrive.
- You were second?

1150
00:53:48,266 --> 00:53:50,310
The two of us were lying down
when you got here?

1151
00:53:50,393 --> 00:53:53,313
I was like, "Wh-What are they doing?
What is going on here?"

1152
00:53:53,813 --> 00:53:56,650
I walked in, and she was casting
some kind of spell on you.

1153
00:53:57,692 --> 00:53:59,611
So I thought, "What is this? Hypnosis?"

1154
00:54:00,237 --> 00:54:03,448
Oh. Well, maybe
that helped them relax a little.

1155
00:54:03,531 --> 00:54:04,658
Right, yep.

1156
00:54:05,825 --> 00:54:07,786
THE MEN DON'T KNOW
WHO IS THE TOP OR SECOND PICK

1157
00:54:07,869 --> 00:54:08,954
Well, this is new.

1158
00:54:09,037 --> 00:54:10,705
- This gathering, that is.
- It really is.

1159
00:54:14,125 --> 00:54:17,504
My current top pick is Jin-woo.

1160
00:54:17,587 --> 00:54:21,883
My date with Jin-woo was the one
that left the biggest impression on me.

1161
00:54:21,967 --> 00:54:26,805
And I guess Jin-woo was the one I kind of
felt a bit of romantic attraction to.

1162
00:54:26,888 --> 00:54:28,640
That's why he's still my top pick.

1163
00:54:30,767 --> 00:54:32,310
My second pick is Seung-hyun,

1164
00:54:32,394 --> 00:54:35,021
as he's the one who's the most cheerful
when talking to me.

1165
00:54:35,105 --> 00:54:36,690
And he also told me
he wanted to talk to me.

1166
00:54:36,773 --> 00:54:39,317
They were each other's top picks
for the first impression vote.

1167
00:54:39,401 --> 00:54:40,735
So, this gathering came to be…

1168
00:54:43,905 --> 00:54:46,783
because I chose you as my top pick
and you as my second pick.

1169
00:54:46,866 --> 00:54:48,868
- Wow, really?
- So that's why we're here. Yeah.

1170
00:54:48,952 --> 00:54:51,538
- So you summoned us here, huh?
- I summoned you here.

1171
00:54:51,621 --> 00:54:55,834
That's why I left first, and I'm guessing
that's why you had to come here.

1172
00:54:55,917 --> 00:54:56,918
I see.

1173
00:54:57,002 --> 00:54:59,170
Oh, she's just straight up telling them.

1174
00:55:03,591 --> 00:55:06,261
I told them
that they were my top and second picks.

1175
00:55:06,761 --> 00:55:09,597
They were just like, "Oh, okay."

1176
00:55:12,851 --> 00:55:15,061
So, the two of you,
how much do you care about distance?

1177
00:55:15,145 --> 00:55:17,105
Well, Soo-hyun lives in Daegu.

1178
00:55:17,188 --> 00:55:19,899
It makes sense
she's thinking about logistics.

1179
00:55:19,983 --> 00:55:23,862
Well, for me, if I really…
if I really came to like someone…

1180
00:55:23,945 --> 00:55:25,405
If you really like them.

1181
00:55:25,488 --> 00:55:27,282
…traveling to see them…

1182
00:55:28,408 --> 00:55:30,577
- Would be fun?
- I think I'd be okay with it.

1183
00:55:31,202 --> 00:55:32,829
Hmm, I see.

1184
00:55:34,414 --> 00:55:35,498
Mm-hmm.

1185
00:55:36,166 --> 00:55:37,542
How about you?

1186
00:55:39,252 --> 00:55:41,629
I've never given this any thought.
It's a no either way?

1187
00:55:42,213 --> 00:55:44,466
- Right, if we lived too far apart…
- If it's too far.

1188
00:55:44,549 --> 00:55:46,343
- …it could be inconvenient.
- Uh-huh. Totally.

1189
00:55:49,596 --> 00:55:53,308
I asked them what they thought
about long-distance relationships.

1190
00:55:53,391 --> 00:55:55,685
Seung-hyun said he would be fine with it.

1191
00:55:55,769 --> 00:55:59,773
But Jin-woo looked unsure,
which added to my concerns.

1192
00:56:00,440 --> 00:56:02,942
The thing is, I thought having
more conversations

1193
00:56:03,026 --> 00:56:05,153
would help clear some things up,

1194
00:56:05,236 --> 00:56:09,032
but instead, they left me with more things
to think about and consider.

1195
00:56:09,115 --> 00:56:11,534
- And I think I struggled with that.
- Mmm.

1196
00:56:11,618 --> 00:56:13,661
Regardless, I think I preferred
how she told them

1197
00:56:13,745 --> 00:56:17,082
that Jin-woo was her top pick
and Seung-hyun was her second pick.

1198
00:56:17,665 --> 00:56:20,543
But Jin-woo's response was lukewarm
at best, don't you think?

1199
00:56:20,627 --> 00:56:21,878
- I know.
- Definitely.

1200
00:56:21,961 --> 00:56:25,256
Basically, Jin-woo wasn't really
responding to anyone other than Su-ji.

1201
00:56:25,340 --> 00:56:27,467
- She's his current top pick.
- Making his heart flutter.

1202
00:56:27,550 --> 00:56:28,843
- You're right.
- She does.

1203
00:56:33,431 --> 00:56:34,432
Wine?

1204
00:56:35,850 --> 00:56:37,102
Han-ju!

1205
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:39,354
HAN-JU'S THREE-WAY DATE

1206
00:56:39,437 --> 00:56:42,107
- The date hasn't even started yet, Han-ju.
- Drinking already?

1207
00:56:47,445 --> 00:56:48,863
Girl, it's still bright out.

1208
00:56:48,947 --> 00:56:51,324
- She drinks well on her own.
- Mm-hmm.

1209
00:56:55,120 --> 00:56:56,204
Who could it be?

1210
00:56:56,287 --> 00:56:58,540
- It's Hyuk-joon, isn't it?
- Jin-woo?

1211
00:57:00,375 --> 00:57:01,876
- Hello.
- Hello.

1212
00:57:01,960 --> 00:57:04,045
Whoa, that's quite the setup
you're enjoying.

1213
00:57:04,129 --> 00:57:06,131
- Take a seat over there.
- Hyuk-joon? Oh.

1214
00:57:06,214 --> 00:57:08,341
They picked a spot that suits each of us.

1215
00:57:08,425 --> 00:57:11,469
She did express her feelings clearly
during the one-on-one Rotation Date.

1216
00:57:11,553 --> 00:57:13,179
Wow, this is so cool.

1217
00:57:14,305 --> 00:57:17,767
I was really surprised
that Han-ju still had feelings for me.

1218
00:57:17,851 --> 00:57:21,771
It feels good, of course,
having someone tell you they like you.

1219
00:57:23,398 --> 00:57:25,775
So, you knew
you'd be coming here, didn't you?

1220
00:57:25,859 --> 00:57:26,860
I didn't.

1221
00:57:26,943 --> 00:57:27,944
- You didn't?
- No.

1222
00:57:28,027 --> 00:57:29,028
I told you yesterday.

1223
00:57:29,112 --> 00:57:30,280
- Oh, you did.
- Yep.

1224
00:57:30,363 --> 00:57:32,782
But remember what you said to me
at the end as you were leaving?

1225
00:57:32,866 --> 00:57:33,950
What did I say?

1226
00:57:34,033 --> 00:57:38,913
You said something along the lines of,
"Let's talk again if we get the chance."

1227
00:57:38,997 --> 00:57:43,001
And "if we get the chance" to me
sounds kind of like "if luck allows."

1228
00:57:43,084 --> 00:57:47,005
So I came to think, "Ah, Han-ju doesn't
have any feelings for me anymore."

1229
00:57:47,088 --> 00:57:49,757
I guess it could be interpreted that way.

1230
00:57:49,841 --> 00:57:53,636
But I actually… I meant it as,
"We should definitely go on a date."

1231
00:57:53,720 --> 00:57:55,180
- Ooh!
- I'm honored.

1232
00:57:55,263 --> 00:57:56,431
She's just so cool.

1233
00:57:56,514 --> 00:57:58,558
You've been on a lot of them, huh?

1234
00:57:58,641 --> 00:58:00,310
Uh, not exactly a lot, but yeah.

1235
00:58:00,852 --> 00:58:02,353
You know what kind of date this is, right?

1236
00:58:02,437 --> 00:58:03,605
I have a rough idea.

1237
00:58:03,688 --> 00:58:07,150
But I figured you'd be pretty busy
going on tour today.

1238
00:58:08,735 --> 00:58:10,403
Oh, what do you mean, "going on tour"?

1239
00:58:10,487 --> 00:58:12,363
But I am right.
You made your rounds already.

1240
00:58:12,447 --> 00:58:14,032
No, I didn't, really.

1241
00:58:14,115 --> 00:58:15,116
Oh, really?

1242
00:58:15,617 --> 00:58:16,784
Such a liar.

1243
00:58:19,746 --> 00:58:22,582
Whoa, it's Jin-woo.

1244
00:58:27,378 --> 00:58:28,922
You must be cold.

1245
00:58:30,006 --> 00:58:32,050
These two are slightly varied
in their appeal.

1246
00:58:32,717 --> 00:58:33,801
You're late.

1247
00:58:35,345 --> 00:58:37,597
- Ah, I'm a little late.
- Ah, you are late.

1248
00:58:38,097 --> 00:58:41,684
I got the feeling someone
was approaching from afar, so I looked.

1249
00:58:41,768 --> 00:58:43,853
And Jin-woo was already smiling.

1250
00:58:43,937 --> 00:58:46,940
But with Han-ju,
I was the one who arrived first,

1251
00:58:47,023 --> 00:58:48,608
so I think I'm the top pick.

1252
00:58:48,691 --> 00:58:53,321
Currently, my top pick is Jin-woo,
and my second pick is Hyuk-joon.

1253
00:58:54,656 --> 00:58:56,616
Arrival order doesn't always
affect the rankings.

1254
00:58:56,699 --> 00:58:58,159
Han-ju was very clear about it.

1255
00:58:59,869 --> 00:59:04,123
Jin-woo's face
is the closest to my ideal type.

1256
00:59:04,207 --> 00:59:07,168
Seriously, his face, though.
He looks like Lai Kuan-lin, right?

1257
00:59:07,252 --> 00:59:09,671
He really looks exactly like Lai Kuan-lin.

1258
00:59:09,754 --> 00:59:14,676
But in terms of looks, the face alone,
you're more my type than anyone else.

1259
00:59:14,759 --> 00:59:16,177
I mean, you're really good-looking.

1260
00:59:17,971 --> 00:59:21,766
I was happy because this was
another opportunity to talk to Jin-woo.

1261
00:59:21,849 --> 00:59:23,268
I was really interested in him.

1262
00:59:23,351 --> 00:59:24,727
But then, there's Hyuk-joon,

1263
00:59:24,811 --> 00:59:26,646
and there's a lot
we hadn't talked about yet.

1264
00:59:26,729 --> 00:59:28,856
I wanted to have
a basic conversation with him.

1265
00:59:28,940 --> 00:59:31,025
So I'm the most curious about him.

1266
00:59:31,609 --> 00:59:33,570
JIN-WOO
HAN-JU'S TOP PICK

1267
00:59:34,862 --> 00:59:35,863
Really?

1268
00:59:35,947 --> 00:59:37,282
HYUK-JOON
HAN-JU'S SECOND PICK

1269
00:59:38,241 --> 00:59:40,118
So how many dates
have you been on, Jin-woo?

1270
00:59:40,201 --> 00:59:41,369
Have I been on many dates?

1271
00:59:41,452 --> 00:59:42,829
Yeah. You have, haven't you?

1272
00:59:42,912 --> 00:59:44,372
Just the right number, I guess?

1273
00:59:44,455 --> 00:59:45,456
So-so.

1274
00:59:45,540 --> 00:59:47,166
I have pretty high standards,

1275
00:59:47,250 --> 00:59:50,753
so I was guessing I might have picked
the most popular men.

1276
00:59:50,837 --> 00:59:53,590
So that's why you thought I've been
on a lot of dates before coming here?

1277
00:59:53,673 --> 00:59:55,967
- Uh-huh. That's why I got here so late.
- I see.

1278
00:59:56,467 --> 00:59:58,219
I'd like some more wine, please.

1279
00:59:59,554 --> 01:00:00,555
Sure.

1280
01:00:01,472 --> 01:00:02,640
- Is that enough?
- Yes.

1281
01:00:02,724 --> 01:00:04,601
Is Han-ju really the only one drinking?

1282
01:00:04,684 --> 01:00:06,352
How much can you drink, by the way?

1283
01:00:07,353 --> 01:00:09,731
- Maybe a bottle of soju?
- A bottle?

1284
01:00:09,814 --> 01:00:11,399
The real answer's two.

1285
01:00:11,482 --> 01:00:13,401
- And a half.
- Okay, so three bottles, then.

1286
01:00:13,484 --> 01:00:15,445
- Oh, one bottle and a half?
- Ma'am!

1287
01:00:15,528 --> 01:00:17,155
- Keeps going up little by little.
- Uh-huh.

1288
01:00:17,238 --> 01:00:20,033
If you can drink a bottle and a half,
you can drink up to two bottles.

1289
01:00:20,116 --> 01:00:22,952
If she puts her mind to it, she can handle
two bottles while staying sober.

1290
01:00:23,036 --> 01:00:25,580
But the thing is,
people here drink less than I thought.

1291
01:00:25,663 --> 01:00:27,915
- Way less than I thought they would.
- I know, right?

1292
01:00:27,999 --> 01:00:30,209
But here I am, with the two of you,

1293
01:00:30,293 --> 01:00:33,254
since you're the only ones
who clink glasses with me.

1294
01:00:33,338 --> 01:00:34,464
I'm grateful for that.

1295
01:00:37,216 --> 01:00:41,137
So is your heart still where it was
in the beginning, <i>noona</i>?

1296
01:00:43,681 --> 01:00:47,644
The two of you are the only ones
I've been considering since the beginning.

1297
01:00:47,727 --> 01:00:49,062
Oh…

1298
01:00:49,145 --> 01:00:50,605
Mmm…

1299
01:00:51,522 --> 01:00:54,067
- You do seem pretty steadfast.
- Mm-hmm.

1300
01:00:54,150 --> 01:00:57,111
If the men get to pick
who they go on a date with,

1301
01:00:57,195 --> 01:00:59,405
do you think you'll choose your top pick

1302
01:00:59,489 --> 01:01:03,242
or someone you would like
to get to know a little bit better?

1303
01:01:03,326 --> 01:01:06,371
- I'd go with my top pick at this point.
- At this point?

1304
01:01:06,454 --> 01:01:08,706
I'd choose the person
I want to talk to more.

1305
01:01:09,207 --> 01:01:10,208
The thing is,

1306
01:01:10,291 --> 01:01:13,211
I think it's a little premature
to decide who your top pick is.

1307
01:01:13,294 --> 01:01:17,632
Geez, despite having mentioned fate
more times than anyone else here…

1308
01:01:17,715 --> 01:01:18,716
Hyuk-joon.

1309
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:20,218
Mm-hmm.

1310
01:01:20,301 --> 01:01:23,721
I feel like I shouldn't put
too much meaning into things.

1311
01:01:23,805 --> 01:01:24,639
Mm-hmm.

1312
01:01:24,722 --> 01:01:26,641
And I've been thinking
about what kind of person

1313
01:01:26,724 --> 01:01:28,142
would genuinely be a good fit for me.

1314
01:01:28,226 --> 01:01:29,852
Mm-hmm.

1315
01:01:32,605 --> 01:01:35,358
Ah, but this sort of thing,
I think it's a good opportunity.

1316
01:01:35,441 --> 01:01:38,111
I've been dying to find out
what other people are thinking.

1317
01:01:38,194 --> 01:01:40,780
I have doubts about people here.
I'm only sure about my own feelings.

1318
01:01:40,863 --> 01:01:44,075
- I have a question about my feelings too.
- I feel the same way, actually.

1319
01:01:44,158 --> 01:01:45,535
Really?

1320
01:01:46,035 --> 01:01:50,581
You seemed to have a lot yesterday.
Have you narrowed down your list or…

1321
01:01:51,290 --> 01:01:53,751
I certainly haven't added anyone to it.

1322
01:01:53,835 --> 01:01:55,753
But I did have one date

1323
01:01:55,837 --> 01:01:58,965
that made me feel like
I shouldn't even bother with that person.

1324
01:01:59,048 --> 01:02:00,049
Mm-hmm.

1325
01:02:00,758 --> 01:02:04,637
But otherwise,
no one has been eliminated from my list.

1326
01:02:04,721 --> 01:02:06,556
It's so hard to make a decision.

1327
01:02:06,639 --> 01:02:09,767
Each of them have their own
little quirks and charms.

1328
01:02:09,851 --> 01:02:11,936
He's definitely being cautious.

1329
01:02:17,150 --> 01:02:19,318
Oh, poor Han-ju doesn't know
where to look.

1330
01:02:19,402 --> 01:02:22,113
- Do you have any questions?
- I was about to ask that as well.

1331
01:02:22,196 --> 01:02:23,614
Oh, I was just about to ask that.

1332
01:02:23,698 --> 01:02:25,324
Oh, were we all?

1333
01:02:25,408 --> 01:02:27,952
Since neither guy is showing
much initiative, it's a bit…

1334
01:02:28,035 --> 01:02:29,328
Right, right.

1335
01:02:29,912 --> 01:02:33,916
So is this the quietest venue
you two have visited on tour so far?

1336
01:02:34,000 --> 01:02:37,712
- But it can't be helped.
- Oh, man. I don't know what to say.

1337
01:02:39,046 --> 01:02:43,217
Jin-woo seemed to be considering
a lot of different women

1338
01:02:43,301 --> 01:02:45,261
as potential options.

1339
01:02:45,344 --> 01:02:47,930
So it made me pretty anxious and uneasy.

1340
01:02:48,014 --> 01:02:51,559
Hyuk-joon implied
he was a little open to options.

1341
01:02:51,642 --> 01:02:55,313
And out of everything he said,
that left the biggest impression on me.

1342
01:02:55,396 --> 01:02:56,939
It made me unsure

1343
01:02:57,023 --> 01:03:00,902
whether it was okay for me
to openly express my feelings for him,

1344
01:03:00,985 --> 01:03:02,570
or if I should just give up.

1345
01:03:03,863 --> 01:03:05,948
Oh, God. Girl, don't chug it like…

1346
01:03:06,657 --> 01:03:10,369
I went there expecting
something like that.

1347
01:03:10,453 --> 01:03:13,998
But I still struggled
to find the right words.

1348
01:03:14,624 --> 01:03:16,626
So I was really at a loss.

1349
01:03:18,920 --> 01:03:22,006
Wow, drinking by herself
with two men seated at her table.

1350
01:03:23,049 --> 01:03:25,134
You two haven't overlapped, have you?

1351
01:03:25,218 --> 01:03:26,969
Are you asking
if we've been on the same date?

1352
01:03:27,053 --> 01:03:28,054
Yep.

1353
01:03:29,138 --> 01:03:30,598
Have they?

1354
01:03:34,560 --> 01:03:35,561
We have.

1355
01:03:35,645 --> 01:03:36,854
Really?

1356
01:03:36,938 --> 01:03:38,105
When was this?

1357
01:03:38,773 --> 01:03:41,234
2 HOURS AGO

1358
01:03:43,486 --> 01:03:44,612
Huh?

1359
01:03:44,695 --> 01:03:46,531
JEONG-EUN'S THREE-WAY DATE

1360
01:03:48,908 --> 01:03:50,159
Oh, nice to see you.

1361
01:03:54,247 --> 01:03:58,835
I was happy because she was one of
the people I was hoping to get picked by.

1362
01:03:58,918 --> 01:04:01,170
So I was stoked she actually picked me.

1363
01:04:01,254 --> 01:04:04,423
Yeah, I was over the moon
when I walked in and saw her there.

1364
01:04:04,507 --> 01:04:07,051
- Jin-woo's second pick was Jeong-eun?
- Yep.

1365
01:04:07,552 --> 01:04:09,095
I took a seat first.

1366
01:04:10,972 --> 01:04:12,431
JIN-WOO
JEONG-EUN'S SECOND PICK

1367
01:04:12,515 --> 01:04:14,684
Jin-woo's second pick, huh?
And he's the top pick.

1368
01:04:14,767 --> 01:04:16,769
I did have suspicions
when I saw two chairs.

1369
01:04:16,853 --> 01:04:19,146
I knew something was off
when they mentioned three-way dates.

1370
01:04:19,230 --> 01:04:21,482
I said I would take
a three-legged race over this.

1371
01:04:21,566 --> 01:04:23,234
- Over this.
- That would've been preferable.

1372
01:04:23,317 --> 01:04:26,362
- His facial expression shifted quickly.
- It's changed drastically, hasn't it?

1373
01:04:26,445 --> 01:04:28,990
- We knew when we were coming here…
- Mm-hmm?

1374
01:04:29,073 --> 01:04:31,534
…that we'd be summoned
if the other person picked us.

1375
01:04:32,285 --> 01:04:35,788
So, to be honest, on my way here,
I was thinking it would be great

1376
01:04:35,872 --> 01:04:39,292
if I got to come here because I was picked
by someone I was interested in.

1377
01:04:39,375 --> 01:04:42,503
- And the thing is, I also picked you.
- Oh, really? Oh.

1378
01:04:42,587 --> 01:04:44,797
I voted for you
when we ended up going together.

1379
01:04:44,881 --> 01:04:47,008
- Expressing himself very freely.
- Telling her right away.

1380
01:04:47,091 --> 01:04:49,218
- Bold. I like it.
- I was surprised when I walked in.

1381
01:04:49,302 --> 01:04:50,469
I walked in here going, "Oh!"

1382
01:04:50,553 --> 01:04:52,054
Oh, so you weren't expecting this?

1383
01:04:52,138 --> 01:04:54,599
I wasn't. That's why
I was really confused yesterday.

1384
01:04:54,682 --> 01:04:56,601
Oh, you went, "What's going on?"

1385
01:04:56,684 --> 01:04:58,519
I was, uh, completely clueless

1386
01:04:58,603 --> 01:05:00,897
as to what the people
I was interested in were thinking.

1387
01:05:00,980 --> 01:05:03,608
And as for the others, well,
I didn't know how to act around them, so…

1388
01:05:04,358 --> 01:05:06,569
Jin-woo bothers me too, actually.

1389
01:05:06,652 --> 01:05:11,574
Yesterday, he even got to go to, uh,
Sparks House, was it? Sparks House.

1390
01:05:11,657 --> 01:05:13,200
He's just a popular guy.

1391
01:05:13,868 --> 01:05:18,039
So I thought the other female contestants
might all flock to him like this.

1392
01:05:21,959 --> 01:05:23,169
Do you like taking pictures?

1393
01:05:23,252 --> 01:05:25,755
- I don't really take many pictures.
- Oh.

1394
01:05:30,134 --> 01:05:32,637
I have a camera at home,
but I don't get to use it that often,

1395
01:05:32,720 --> 01:05:35,014
so it's just been sitting there
gathering dust recently.

1396
01:05:35,097 --> 01:05:37,016
- Out of nowhere.
- Aren't cameras expensive?

1397
01:05:37,099 --> 01:05:39,143
- What is he doing?
- It's not an expensive model.

1398
01:05:39,226 --> 01:05:42,063
- I'm no expert by any means.
- Hold up. No. Put that back. Put it away.

1399
01:05:42,146 --> 01:05:43,773
I hope he's not planning
to show her a picture.

1400
01:05:43,856 --> 01:05:45,107
I don't get to…

1401
01:05:46,651 --> 01:05:48,277
I was worried this might happen.

1402
01:05:48,361 --> 01:05:50,404
<i>Wah wah wah wah </i>

1403
01:05:50,488 --> 01:05:51,989
Hyuk-joon has a tendency to…

1404
01:05:52,073 --> 01:05:54,325
Okay, like when he bragged
that he climbed Hallasan

1405
01:05:54,408 --> 01:05:57,328
without taking a single break
when they were talking about hiking, or--

1406
01:05:57,411 --> 01:05:58,496
"I even brought this thing."

1407
01:05:58,579 --> 01:06:00,915
Doesn't say anything, just pulls out
his phone and finds evidence.

1408
01:06:00,998 --> 01:06:02,458
I was like, "No, he wouldn't."

1409
01:06:02,541 --> 01:06:04,043
- No one even asked him.
- This is…

1410
01:06:04,126 --> 01:06:05,711
And it was just a picture
of a tree and the sky.

1411
01:06:05,795 --> 01:06:07,922
I thought he'd at least show off
something impressive.

1412
01:06:10,549 --> 01:06:12,176
That's pretty. When did you take it?

1413
01:06:12,259 --> 01:06:13,636
I took it back at the dorm.

1414
01:06:13,719 --> 01:06:15,596
- Oh, where the tree is?
- Oh, really?

1415
01:06:16,764 --> 01:06:18,516
I'm into this sort of thing. And…

1416
01:06:19,016 --> 01:06:20,768
- The prince.
- When he was playing the piano?

1417
01:06:20,851 --> 01:06:23,187
- Good photo. He looks cool.
- Like a legendary figure.

1418
01:06:24,063 --> 01:06:26,607
I was kind of hyperconscious of Hyuk-joon.

1419
01:06:26,691 --> 01:06:29,819
We hadn't really talked much
outside of the wider group,

1420
01:06:29,902 --> 01:06:31,153
so I wasn't close to him.

1421
01:06:31,237 --> 01:06:35,074
And honestly, since he was
quite a bit older than me and taller,

1422
01:06:35,157 --> 01:06:39,578
I felt a bit intimidated by him and all,
which is why I felt conscious of him.

1423
01:06:39,662 --> 01:06:41,330
Those two are very different people.

1424
01:06:41,414 --> 01:06:43,332
Leave the photos to me.
Are you into photography?

1425
01:06:43,416 --> 01:06:44,875
- Mm-hmm.
- Oh.

1426
01:06:44,959 --> 01:06:47,169
- I love taking photos.
- Mm-hmm.

1427
01:06:50,965 --> 01:06:54,510
So are you pretty firmly into
just your top and second picks, then?

1428
01:06:54,593 --> 01:06:55,928
Or are the others…

1429
01:06:56,012 --> 01:06:56,887
So far.

1430
01:06:56,971 --> 01:06:59,974
- You aren't really attracted to them yet?
- Uh-uh. I just don't know. Uh-uh.

1431
01:07:01,100 --> 01:07:02,101
I was happy

1432
01:07:02,184 --> 01:07:05,229
because I felt I'd gotten to know how
the person I'd been curious about felt.

1433
01:07:05,312 --> 01:07:06,397
That look in his eyes.

1434
01:07:07,398 --> 01:07:08,399
I felt relieved.

1435
01:07:08,482 --> 01:07:10,818
Kind of like one of my question marks
had been resolved,

1436
01:07:10,901 --> 01:07:11,986
which was the best part.

1437
01:07:12,570 --> 01:07:14,447
When it comes to Jeong-eun,

1438
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:17,950
I feel like we just clicked better
in terms of hobbies.

1439
01:07:18,034 --> 01:07:23,122
But, um, I don't think she had
that kind of chemistry with Jin-woo.

1440
01:07:23,873 --> 01:07:26,250
Oh, they're both keeping
an eye on each other.

1441
01:07:26,333 --> 01:07:29,128
- Wow, Hyuk-joon's kind of…
- He's changed.

1442
01:07:29,211 --> 01:07:31,380
Oh, Hyuk-joon had his eye on the prize.

1443
01:07:31,464 --> 01:07:34,341
But when others started
showing interest in him, he went,

1444
01:07:34,425 --> 01:07:36,343
"Huh, am I more attractive
than I thought I was?"

1445
01:07:36,427 --> 01:07:37,678
Ah, yes.

1446
01:07:37,762 --> 01:07:41,015
- I know, right? That's the vibe. Totally.
- I am kind of getting that vibe from him.

1447
01:07:41,098 --> 01:07:42,433
And he seems to be very confident

1448
01:07:42,516 --> 01:07:44,727
that he's the top pick
in every situation right now.

1449
01:07:44,810 --> 01:07:48,355
- Yes, I think you're right.
- He's gotten a bit… a bit cocky.

1450
01:07:48,439 --> 01:07:50,316
- Cocky.
- This is a big change.

1451
01:08:00,117 --> 01:08:01,118
HYUN-SEO'S THREE-WAY DATE

1452
01:08:01,202 --> 01:08:03,662
- Yes, I'm curious about Hyun-seo.
- Hyun-seo… Oh, her.

1453
01:08:11,962 --> 01:08:15,633
I was really nervous.
I was nervous, I felt like throwing up.

1454
01:08:15,716 --> 01:08:19,095
And although I was hungry,
I didn't feel like eating at all.

1455
01:08:20,387 --> 01:08:21,388
Who's up?

1456
01:08:22,014 --> 01:08:23,641
From the back it could be…

1457
01:08:29,855 --> 01:08:32,024
- It's Seung-hyun.
- Ah, it's Seung-hyun.

1458
01:08:32,608 --> 01:08:34,193
Hello.

1459
01:08:36,946 --> 01:08:38,948
SEUNG-HYUN
HYUN-SEO'S SECOND PICK

1460
01:08:40,449 --> 01:08:41,951
You haven't had anything to eat yet?

1461
01:08:42,034 --> 01:08:43,494
I don't have much of an appetite.

1462
01:08:43,577 --> 01:08:45,579
Oh, you don't? No appetite, really?

1463
01:08:45,663 --> 01:08:47,206
- No.
- To be honest…

1464
01:08:48,707 --> 01:08:51,919
ye-yesterday, uh,
during the ten-minute date,

1465
01:08:53,379 --> 01:08:55,172
you mentioned that, um…

1466
01:08:55,256 --> 01:08:56,257
What?

1467
01:08:57,174 --> 01:08:59,593
- You thought it was Su-ji.
- Huh?

1468
01:09:00,177 --> 01:09:01,971
At the time, she actually wasn't.

1469
01:09:02,054 --> 01:09:03,097
Uh-huh.

1470
01:09:03,681 --> 01:09:05,307
Is he going to say, "It's actually Su-ji"?

1471
01:09:05,391 --> 01:09:07,768
Oh, at the time, I, uh, you know…

1472
01:09:07,852 --> 01:09:10,646
I said I wasn't really, you know,
attracted to her or whatever.

1473
01:09:11,647 --> 01:09:14,608
But the truth be told,
during the ten-minute date…

1474
01:09:15,943 --> 01:09:18,445
things kind of changed a little.

1475
01:09:18,946 --> 01:09:19,780
Sure. Great.

1476
01:09:19,864 --> 01:09:21,490
- Bring that up the moment you sit down.
- I know.

1477
01:09:21,574 --> 01:09:23,325
So you're attracted to Su-ji?

1478
01:09:23,826 --> 01:09:28,205
Um, uh, I just thought it… it might seem
as though I had lied about it back then,

1479
01:09:28,289 --> 01:09:30,166
so it bothered me a little.

1480
01:09:30,249 --> 01:09:33,169
So I just want to say that's not it.

1481
01:09:33,252 --> 01:09:35,421
I really thought there was
nothing between us back then.

1482
01:09:35,504 --> 01:09:36,463
Mm-hmm.

1483
01:09:36,547 --> 01:09:39,300
But I think an attraction
kind of developed…

1484
01:09:39,383 --> 01:09:41,844
- With Su-ji?
- …during the ten-minute date.

1485
01:09:41,927 --> 01:09:44,763
So, um, uh, I thought
you might misunderstand

1486
01:09:44,847 --> 01:09:46,724
and think that I had
kind of lied about it.

1487
01:09:46,807 --> 01:09:49,643
- No, it's okay. You don't have to worry.
- Oh, really? I was a little worried.

1488
01:09:49,727 --> 01:09:51,061
These things happen.

1489
01:09:52,104 --> 01:09:55,900
Actually, I looked at your diary
at the 5 Minute Library today.

1490
01:09:55,983 --> 01:09:57,067
- Oh, really?
- Uh-huh.

1491
01:09:57,151 --> 01:10:01,280
So I knew you were attracted to Su-ji.

1492
01:10:03,282 --> 01:10:06,702
I mean, well, I wasn't disappointed
in him or anything.

1493
01:10:06,785 --> 01:10:10,372
I just figured he was concerned
that he might come off as a liar.

1494
01:10:11,207 --> 01:10:15,294
But now, I'm at the point where,
uh, I don't really care.

1495
01:10:16,921 --> 01:10:19,423
I think it means she has
no feelings for him whatsoever.

1496
01:10:19,506 --> 01:10:21,133
I can see why she might've been put off.

1497
01:10:21,217 --> 01:10:22,968
- They haven't even gathered yet.
- Right.

1498
01:10:30,643 --> 01:10:31,852
Who could this be?

1499
01:10:38,692 --> 01:10:40,236
Oh, he's here.

1500
01:10:43,113 --> 01:10:44,865
- Hyuk-joon?
- Hello.

1501
01:10:44,949 --> 01:10:46,116
HYUK-JOON
HYUN-SEO'S TOP PICK

1502
01:10:46,200 --> 01:10:48,327
Hyuk-joon has gone on four dates now,
including this one.

1503
01:10:48,410 --> 01:10:51,622
- Got this strut. Get a load of this guy.
- Hands in his pockets.

1504
01:10:54,083 --> 01:10:56,627
I kind of felt as though
I had wronged Hyuk-joon in a way.

1505
01:10:56,710 --> 01:10:57,795
What? How?

1506
01:10:57,878 --> 01:11:01,799
Because he must be thinking, "Oh,
Hyun-seo's interested in that person."

1507
01:11:02,967 --> 01:11:05,761
I didn't feel great about it.

1508
01:11:09,014 --> 01:11:11,976
I had been, uh, curious
about Hyun-seo's second pick,

1509
01:11:12,059 --> 01:11:14,228
and it felt like a very rational choice.

1510
01:11:14,311 --> 01:11:17,773
Seung-hyun has a different
brand of charm from me,

1511
01:11:17,856 --> 01:11:19,900
so I wasn't too surprised.

1512
01:11:21,610 --> 01:11:24,363
Were you summoned here and there a lot?

1513
01:11:24,446 --> 01:11:27,491
- He's got this air of confidence.
- I know, right?

1514
01:11:27,574 --> 01:11:28,575
How was it?

1515
01:11:29,076 --> 01:11:32,121
- So today-- Me too, me too.
- Yeah, kind of, kind of. Mm-hmm.

1516
01:11:32,204 --> 01:11:33,497
I've been around.

1517
01:11:34,665 --> 01:11:37,084
There's a difference in his energy
around Hyun-seo, right?

1518
01:11:37,167 --> 01:11:39,003
- They're not even talking.
- It's changed.

1519
01:11:39,712 --> 01:11:42,172
Oh, this question's just sprung to mind.

1520
01:11:42,256 --> 01:11:45,175
Out of all the dates
you've been on so far,

1521
01:11:45,259 --> 01:11:47,261
were there any particularly
memorable ones?

1522
01:11:47,344 --> 01:11:50,514
Okay. Hyun-seo's directing
this question at Hyuk-joon.

1523
01:11:52,057 --> 01:11:56,478
I think yesterday's ten-minute dates
were the most memorable for me.

1524
01:11:56,562 --> 01:11:57,855
Mm-hmm.

1525
01:11:57,938 --> 01:11:58,897
Yep.

1526
01:11:58,981 --> 01:12:00,232
Wh-What about you?

1527
01:12:00,316 --> 01:12:02,943
I guess it's yesterday's
ten-minute dates for me too.

1528
01:12:03,027 --> 01:12:04,236
Huh?

1529
01:12:04,320 --> 01:12:07,906
Anyway, some of the things she kept
talking about really surprised me.

1530
01:12:08,824 --> 01:12:12,369
Oh, God.
Why in the world is he doing this?

1531
01:12:12,953 --> 01:12:13,954
Like what?

1532
01:12:14,747 --> 01:12:18,292
Uh, I thought there weren't
any people who were interested.

1533
01:12:18,375 --> 01:12:21,462
So I had been thinking
that no one was curious about me.

1534
01:12:22,046 --> 01:12:23,589
But it was like, "Oh!"

1535
01:12:23,672 --> 01:12:27,801
The responses I got during
the ten-minute dates told me otherwise.

1536
01:12:28,385 --> 01:12:30,012
Good lord.

1537
01:12:30,095 --> 01:12:33,015
So I was like,
"Then why didn't you give me the towel?"

1538
01:12:33,098 --> 01:12:34,099
That kind of thing.

1539
01:12:34,183 --> 01:12:37,895
And then there was also stuff like,
"Why didn't you express your interest?"

1540
01:12:37,978 --> 01:12:43,233
So a lot of surprising things transpired
during the ten-minute dates yesterday.

1541
01:12:44,735 --> 01:12:47,154
- Oh, see, she's thrown off.
- Understandable.

1542
01:12:47,237 --> 01:12:49,740
Why would he respond
to Hyun-seo like that?

1543
01:12:49,823 --> 01:12:51,367
Wow, that was uncalled-for.

1544
01:12:51,450 --> 01:12:53,827
I feel like if I were
to hear this in person,

1545
01:12:53,911 --> 01:12:55,829
my heart would just drop, like, "Thud!"

1546
01:12:55,913 --> 01:12:56,830
I know, right?

1547
01:12:56,914 --> 01:12:59,458
Initially, he had a bunch of stuff
going on with Hyun-seo.

1548
01:12:59,541 --> 01:13:01,710
- Right.
- That's why he kept talking about fate.

1549
01:13:01,794 --> 01:13:03,962
But then, during
the ten-minute dates yesterday,

1550
01:13:04,046 --> 01:13:06,673
he found out the girls
had been interested in him all along.

1551
01:13:06,757 --> 01:13:09,259
And now he's walking around
with his chest puffed up.

1552
01:13:09,343 --> 01:13:11,678
- Exactly.
- That's the source of his transformation.

1553
01:13:11,762 --> 01:13:14,556
It's like having a boyfriend
who's hit it big overnight.

1554
01:13:14,640 --> 01:13:16,642
"Babe, where have you been?"
"Oh, you know…"

1555
01:13:17,935 --> 01:13:20,562
He's giving the energy of a boyfriend
who has better things to do.

1556
01:13:20,646 --> 01:13:22,314
- So bizarre.
- First of all…

1557
01:13:23,399 --> 01:13:25,359
I don't even know what to say, seriously.

1558
01:13:25,442 --> 01:13:29,321
And why did Hyun-seo choose today
of all days to wear that scarf?

1559
01:13:29,405 --> 01:13:32,324
- She looks like a tragic heroine.
- That's exactly it.

1560
01:13:32,408 --> 01:13:34,243
"Excuse me?
Whatever could you mean by that?"

1561
01:13:34,326 --> 01:13:35,744
Nailed the vibe.

1562
01:13:35,828 --> 01:13:37,037
That's exactly what that is.

1563
01:13:37,121 --> 01:13:38,580
"But, Papa, we made a vow!"

1564
01:13:38,664 --> 01:13:41,125
Spot on. Spot on.

1565
01:13:41,208 --> 01:13:44,962
"My dear, I won't be able to return
for a while now that I'm busy."

1566
01:13:45,045 --> 01:13:48,132
"Then what of this ring you gave me?"

1567
01:13:48,215 --> 01:13:50,592
- Oh, God.
- "Do what you will with that ring."

1568
01:13:50,676 --> 01:13:52,845
"Kim Chun-bae, you scoundrel!"

1569
01:13:52,928 --> 01:13:55,139
Now spot the difference.
It's exactly that.

1570
01:13:55,722 --> 01:13:57,808
Do you have a most memorable date?

1571
01:13:58,767 --> 01:14:01,145
I'm going to keep it a secret.

1572
01:14:01,228 --> 01:14:03,063
Of course. She can't bring it up now.

1573
01:14:03,147 --> 01:14:05,107
- We told you ours.
- What is this?

1574
01:14:05,190 --> 01:14:06,650
I'm going to keep it a secret.

1575
01:14:06,733 --> 01:14:08,193
Well, now she's upset.

1576
01:14:08,277 --> 01:14:10,737
There's no fun in revealing everything.

1577
01:14:10,821 --> 01:14:11,864
That's true.

1578
01:14:15,659 --> 01:14:20,873
Okay, let's say someone's
shown a lot of interest in you.

1579
01:14:20,956 --> 01:14:25,085
Do you think your heart would waver,
and you would change your mind?

1580
01:14:25,169 --> 01:14:27,504


1581
01:14:31,508 --> 01:14:32,885
Please watch what you say.

1582
01:14:32,968 --> 01:14:34,344
Shown me a lot of interest?

1583
01:14:34,428 --> 01:14:36,805
Well, I think that would depend
on who it is.

1584
01:14:36,889 --> 01:14:38,140
- Mm-hmm.
- Huh?

1585
01:14:38,849 --> 01:14:41,560
And if they went out of their way
to talk to me and stuff,

1586
01:14:41,643 --> 01:14:45,397
I feel like those kinds of gestures
could make me change my mind.

1587
01:14:45,481 --> 01:14:48,192
- Hold on a minute.
- Why does he keep…

1588
01:14:48,275 --> 01:14:50,652
Oh, Hyun-seo's now… Oh, no.

1589
01:14:50,736 --> 01:14:52,863
She must be feeling so let down.

1590
01:14:52,946 --> 01:14:57,117
I kind of thought, "This is bad.
The race is really on now."

1591
01:14:57,701 --> 01:14:59,286
And I was also a little worried

1592
01:14:59,369 --> 01:15:02,706
because he had gone on dates
with other people as well.

1593
01:15:02,789 --> 01:15:06,543
Especially for Hyuk-joon, since he had
only been on dates with me previously.

1594
01:15:06,627 --> 01:15:10,214
This was his chance to have some
deep conversations with the other women.

1595
01:15:11,798 --> 01:15:16,887
So I thought,
"Maybe his heart could be swayed."

1596
01:15:16,970 --> 01:15:20,974
Well, so you guys have been on dates
with other people today.

1597
01:15:21,975 --> 01:15:23,602
Have you had a change of heart?

1598
01:15:25,312 --> 01:15:27,064
- A change of heart?
- Mm-hmm.

1599
01:15:27,147 --> 01:15:30,108
A change? I don't think
I've had a change of heart. Mm-mmm.

1600
01:15:30,192 --> 01:15:32,152
I wouldn't say I've had
a change of heart, either.

1601
01:15:32,236 --> 01:15:34,530
I just want to hear more
of what the others have to say.

1602
01:15:34,613 --> 01:15:36,990
So they have had an impact on me. Mm-hmm.

1603
01:15:37,491 --> 01:15:41,078
- They surprised me in some ways, you see.
- Oh, right. Actually, yeah.

1604
01:15:41,161 --> 01:15:43,956
- I feel the same way. Yeah, exactly.
- They definitely surprised me.

1605
01:15:45,791 --> 01:15:48,126
I felt that
the road ahead was a little bleak,

1606
01:15:48,210 --> 01:15:51,672
and that things weren't exactly
going to be fun and games.

1607
01:15:51,755 --> 01:15:55,384
So I was worried about
how I should express my feelings.

1608
01:15:55,467 --> 01:15:57,052
But at the same time,

1609
01:15:57,135 --> 01:16:02,599
concerned that expressing my feelings
too much might make me look really easy.

1610
01:16:02,683 --> 01:16:03,809
On the other hand, though,

1611
01:16:03,892 --> 01:16:06,728
not expressing myself puts me
at a risk of losing him to someone else.

1612
01:16:06,812 --> 01:16:08,647
I'm just so confused right now.

1613
01:16:08,730 --> 01:16:10,357
Looks like she's really into him now.

1614
01:16:11,024 --> 01:16:12,192
My feelings?

1615
01:16:13,235 --> 01:16:16,280
It's complicated. But I enjoy it.

1616
01:16:16,363 --> 01:16:19,992
Of course, I do enjoy having women
show their interest in me.

1617
01:16:20,075 --> 01:16:22,703
Well… I did feel a bit bad, though.

1618
01:16:22,786 --> 01:16:26,915
I hadn't so much as glanced
at anyone but Hyun-seo.

1619
01:16:26,999 --> 01:16:30,711
I did really think
that they wouldn't be interested in me.

1620
01:16:31,461 --> 01:16:34,172
And I just ruled them out.

1621
01:16:34,256 --> 01:16:36,967
But now, I've been on dates
with all of them,

1622
01:16:37,050 --> 01:16:38,677
and they all happened to pick me.

1623
01:16:38,760 --> 01:16:41,763
So I can't help but feel
more attracted to them.

1624
01:16:42,264 --> 01:16:43,765
THE THREE-WAY DATES ARE OVER

1625
01:16:43,849 --> 01:16:45,809
- Huh?
- What the heck?

1626
01:16:45,892 --> 01:16:47,436
Things have gotten so complicated.

1627
01:16:47,519 --> 01:16:49,396
- Bye, guys.
- I had a great time.

1628
01:16:49,980 --> 01:16:52,649
- See you later.
- How could he rush off like that?

1629
01:16:56,778 --> 01:16:58,989
All this really did
was confuse Hyun-seo a lot.

1630
01:16:59,072 --> 01:16:59,948
I know.

1631
01:17:00,032 --> 01:17:01,533
She's got a lot on her mind.

1632
01:17:01,617 --> 01:17:04,202
- Hyuk-joon's become really popular.
- Very.

1633
01:17:04,286 --> 01:17:07,080
- He was selected by all four women.
- You're right.

1634
01:17:07,164 --> 01:17:10,375
I don't know if he's playing it safe
so he can change his mind later,

1635
01:17:10,459 --> 01:17:12,544
or if he's telling her to be on her toes.

1636
01:17:12,628 --> 01:17:15,088
This could be how he's feeling.

1637
01:17:15,172 --> 01:17:17,841
Now that these other women
are expressing their interest in him,

1638
01:17:17,924 --> 01:17:19,301
Hyuk-joon could be thinking,

1639
01:17:19,384 --> 01:17:22,888
all these dates with Hyun-seo
and whatnot were going great for her.

1640
01:17:22,971 --> 01:17:26,183
From his point of view, he feels
he was the only one bringing up fate,

1641
01:17:26,266 --> 01:17:28,518
showing his feelings,
and expressing interest in her.

1642
01:17:28,602 --> 01:17:30,646
- And that disappointment--
- Had been bothering him.

1643
01:17:30,729 --> 01:17:33,315
And with the cold incident,
it boiled over.

1644
01:17:33,398 --> 01:17:34,900
"The cold incident."

1645
01:17:34,983 --> 01:17:36,818
- Was that really…
- Man, the cold.

1646
01:17:36,902 --> 01:17:38,695
Was that really such a pivotal event?

1647
01:17:38,779 --> 01:17:40,822
- It's "the cold incident."
- Right.

1648
01:17:40,906 --> 01:17:43,283
It wasn't simply a matter of,
"She showed no concern for my health

1649
01:17:43,367 --> 01:17:44,284
when I had a cold."

1650
01:17:44,368 --> 01:17:45,994
- Yes. And the tumbler?
- Right.

1651
01:17:46,078 --> 01:17:48,955
- But rather, all these pent-up emotions…
- Am I being too harsh right now?

1652
01:17:49,039 --> 01:17:50,582
…when he caught a cold,
made him think,

1653
01:17:50,666 --> 01:17:53,293
"That person really doesn't
express any feelings for me."

1654
01:17:53,377 --> 01:17:55,754
We've got the tumbler incident
on top of the cold incident.

1655
01:17:55,837 --> 01:17:57,964
- Ah, the tumbler incident too.
- That's right.

1656
01:17:58,048 --> 01:18:00,300
So it's a mishmash
of a lot of factors right now.

1657
01:18:00,384 --> 01:18:02,302
And that might be why
he keeps quipping at her.

1658
01:18:02,386 --> 01:18:04,429
He's bothered because
he wants her to show him affection.

1659
01:18:04,513 --> 01:18:06,807
And he's expressing himself
like a pubescent kid would.

1660
01:18:06,890 --> 01:18:10,185
Ah, so he was disappointed about that?
I really can't tell what he's thinking.

1661
01:18:21,530 --> 01:18:24,241
I didn't go on a date today.

1662
01:18:25,575 --> 01:18:29,329
I did think it would be nice
if I could go on a date with Seo-yoon.

1663
01:18:33,083 --> 01:18:35,460
- You're shooting daggers right now.
- Kind of.

1664
01:18:36,628 --> 01:18:42,300
I think I should consider myself
out of the running for Seo-yoon.

1665
01:18:44,511 --> 01:18:49,099
To my understanding, today's date
is supposed to be two men per woman.

1666
01:18:49,182 --> 01:18:51,977
And the woman decides
who the two men will be.

1667
01:18:52,060 --> 01:18:53,061
THIS AFTERNOON

1668
01:18:53,145 --> 01:18:55,605
But, you know, dates are supposed
to be a one-on-one affair.

1669
01:18:55,689 --> 01:18:58,859
I know, right? If dates are supposed
to be one-on-one, that's really not…

1670
01:18:58,942 --> 01:19:00,736
So, it's a little…

1671
01:19:04,072 --> 01:19:05,699
What? He's leaving?

1672
01:19:05,782 --> 01:19:06,742
- He's leaving.
- What?

1673
01:19:06,825 --> 01:19:08,118
- What's this?
- Jin-woo's leaving.

1674
01:19:08,201 --> 01:19:10,287
I guess we're leaving one by one
when we get picked.

1675
01:19:10,370 --> 01:19:11,997
- Oh…
- Right.

1676
01:19:12,080 --> 01:19:13,248
Huh? Oh, wait.

1677
01:19:13,331 --> 01:19:15,375
Shouldn't we take this off?
You got something?

1678
01:19:15,459 --> 01:19:16,668
- Uh-huh.
- Okay. Later, then.

1679
01:19:16,752 --> 01:19:19,337
Oh, no.
Not Jae-seo watching from the side.

1680
01:19:19,421 --> 01:19:22,007
- Really? It wouldn't open.
- I guess they get in touch.

1681
01:19:22,090 --> 01:19:23,216
He said it wouldn't open.

1682
01:19:24,050 --> 01:19:26,219
- I'm off now. Okay.
- Have a safe trip.

1683
01:19:26,303 --> 01:19:28,096
Did you pack everything? Your meds?

1684
01:19:28,180 --> 01:19:29,514
<i>- Hyung</i>?
- Yeah.

1685
01:19:29,598 --> 01:19:31,224
- I'm off.
- What?

1686
01:19:31,808 --> 01:19:33,393
- Oh, okay.
- Okay.

1687
01:19:34,519 --> 01:19:38,940
After seeing all the men
get selected and leaving one by one,

1688
01:19:39,024 --> 01:19:43,069
I kind of assumed that I'm not going
to be picked this time, sadly.

1689
01:19:45,071 --> 01:19:47,240
I knew something like this could happen.

1690
01:19:47,324 --> 01:19:49,159
I'm pretty used to it by now.

1691
01:19:49,242 --> 01:19:51,995
So I just came back, lay down, and slept.

1692
01:20:08,303 --> 01:20:09,930
- Are those tears?
- Is he crying?

1693
01:20:10,430 --> 01:20:12,516
Uh-uh.

1694
01:20:12,599 --> 01:20:14,684
Oh, man, it hurts to see him cry.

1695
01:20:29,157 --> 01:20:32,661
I just kept thinking that
I should have seen this coming.

1696
01:20:32,744 --> 01:20:35,080
Of course I couldn't make this work.

1697
01:20:36,081 --> 01:20:40,961
If I'm completely honest, I always knew
I wouldn't be anyone's top choice vote.

1698
01:20:41,044 --> 01:20:44,589
But I thought I would at least
be someone's second choice.

1699
01:20:44,673 --> 01:20:47,008
This outcome confirmed my insecurities.

1700
01:20:47,092 --> 01:20:48,969
Actually, in the very beginning,

1701
01:20:49,052 --> 01:20:52,764
when they asked me what I was hoping
to take away from being on this show,

1702
01:20:52,848 --> 01:20:56,226
I said that I want to accurately assess
any issues I might have.

1703
01:20:56,309 --> 01:20:59,062
But the problem is that
no one says the same thing.

1704
01:20:59,145 --> 01:21:01,731
"You're a good conversationalist,
but there's this issue."

1705
01:21:01,815 --> 01:21:03,400
Or, "Your looks are the issue."

1706
01:21:03,483 --> 01:21:06,027
"No, his looks are fine,
it's his daily routine."

1707
01:21:06,111 --> 01:21:08,697
So the only answer is that
actually everything is an issue.

1708
01:21:08,780 --> 01:21:12,742
But the point is, I want to define
what is and isn't a problem.

1709
01:21:12,826 --> 01:21:16,872
That may be an occupational quirk of mine,
but I am always focused on improvement.

1710
01:21:17,664 --> 01:21:21,543
I'm a workaholic, so they locked me up
in here and said, "Go have fun."

1711
01:21:21,626 --> 01:21:23,795
But then it's,
"You just need to shave your beard.

1712
01:21:23,879 --> 01:21:24,963
You just need a haircut."

1713
01:21:25,046 --> 01:21:27,674
Then, "There, we've fixed
everything wrong with your looks."

1714
01:21:31,720 --> 01:21:32,929
Since it's still not working,

1715
01:21:33,013 --> 01:21:35,473
that implies an error
in the control variables.

1716
01:21:35,557 --> 01:21:36,683
Based on my calculations,

1717
01:21:36,766 --> 01:21:39,144
I've determined that
once you combine all of my traits,

1718
01:21:39,227 --> 01:21:41,855
the way I talk in general,
the way I treat my friends,

1719
01:21:41,938 --> 01:21:43,231
my vibe, and everything else,

1720
01:21:43,315 --> 01:21:46,192
I'm just not good enough
to make it into the top two.

1721
01:21:49,738 --> 01:21:52,115
I go through a huge turning point
every ten years.

1722
01:21:53,658 --> 01:21:54,951
Hold on. I'm sorry.

1723
01:22:03,084 --> 01:22:04,127
Right.

1724
01:22:11,760 --> 01:22:13,011
Ah, this is…

1725
01:22:14,638 --> 01:22:17,599
This isn't easy.
I really didn't see this coming.

1726
01:22:19,768 --> 01:22:20,894
I mean… Yeah.

1727
01:22:24,022 --> 01:22:28,193
But because I go through some kind of
huge life change every ten years…

1728
01:22:30,153 --> 01:22:32,739
First, I entered into
a ten-year period of study.

1729
01:22:34,658 --> 01:22:36,618
And I assumed studying was my path.

1730
01:22:36,701 --> 01:22:40,455
But then out of nowhere, ten years
of game development came knocking…

1731
01:22:41,790 --> 01:22:43,750
So I'm nearing the ten-year mark again,

1732
01:22:44,751 --> 01:22:47,712
and I kind of feel
as if I've been living my life…

1733
01:22:49,214 --> 01:22:50,548
the wrong way…

1734
01:22:53,635 --> 01:22:55,512
All because I was told it was right.

1735
01:22:57,097 --> 01:22:58,640
You see, but…

1736
01:23:15,949 --> 01:23:17,367
Ah…

1737
01:23:17,450 --> 01:23:20,286
But people kept telling me
that I was doing so well for myself,

1738
01:23:20,370 --> 01:23:22,080
so I thought I made the right call.

1739
01:23:23,373 --> 01:23:25,750
Since no one ever told me
I was doing something wrong,

1740
01:23:25,834 --> 01:23:27,544
I just kept living that way.

1741
01:23:28,837 --> 01:23:30,630
But now, I'm wondering if…

1742
01:23:32,465 --> 01:23:34,050
there even is a right answer.

1743
01:23:37,137 --> 01:23:39,639
I feel like there's just
so much I don't know.

1744
01:23:39,723 --> 01:23:41,099
All I ever focused on was work.

1745
01:23:41,182 --> 01:23:43,351
Work and my studies, that sort of thing.

1746
01:23:43,435 --> 01:23:46,021
And people tell me I'm amazing.
But that's not it.

1747
01:23:46,104 --> 01:23:48,148
They only get to see me at work or school.

1748
01:23:48,648 --> 01:23:51,818
They think that because I funnel
all my energy into those things.

1749
01:23:51,901 --> 01:23:53,445
Because I don't do anything else.

1750
01:23:55,864 --> 01:23:57,157
Other alumni from my school,

1751
01:23:57,240 --> 01:23:59,159
they all find someone,
get married and have kids,

1752
01:23:59,242 --> 01:24:00,827
all while doing what I do.

1753
01:24:00,910 --> 01:24:03,705
Even at my company,
everyone else is taking those steps.

1754
01:24:03,788 --> 01:24:07,751
I used to use the excuse that I went to
an all-boys middle school and high school.

1755
01:24:07,834 --> 01:24:11,212
But other people who did that
get into relationships, so it's like…

1756
01:24:12,589 --> 01:24:15,175
It's possible to do other things
while doing what I do,

1757
01:24:15,258 --> 01:24:17,302
but I can barely manage
to keep up with this,

1758
01:24:17,385 --> 01:24:19,179
which is why I'm just stuck in a rut.

1759
01:24:19,262 --> 01:24:20,388
And it's kind of…

1760
01:24:21,514 --> 01:24:23,600
kind of pathetic of me.

1761
01:24:25,685 --> 01:24:27,645
So that's… that's how it is, yeah.

1762
01:24:40,283 --> 01:24:43,703
I think I've realized
how I should live the next ten years.

1763
01:25:02,013 --> 01:25:07,143
In a way, I think that this show may have
helped Jae-seo find his true self.

1764
01:25:07,227 --> 01:25:08,353
- Right.
- Totally.

1765
01:25:08,436 --> 01:25:10,313
He was praised for being a good student.

1766
01:25:10,396 --> 01:25:13,274
He was praised for getting work
at so-and-so companies.

1767
01:25:13,358 --> 01:25:15,819
- Then it was, "You're good at your job."
- He's a hard worker.

1768
01:25:15,902 --> 01:25:19,030
So this is kind of like that first
real failure he's experienced in life.

1769
01:25:19,114 --> 01:25:21,491
Wow, okay. So in a way,
this could be a chance for him to grow.

1770
01:25:21,574 --> 01:25:22,408
Exactly.

1771
01:25:22,492 --> 01:25:25,036
"I guess I've been too neglectful
of everything apart from work."

1772
01:25:25,120 --> 01:25:26,079
Exactly.

1773
01:25:26,162 --> 01:25:29,290
He's finally realizing that he needs
to take care of those other things.

1774
01:25:29,374 --> 01:25:32,085
He has to foster
his personal life as well.

1775
01:25:32,168 --> 01:25:35,713
- I see so much of myself in Jae-seo.
- This is so sad.

1776
01:25:35,797 --> 01:25:38,049
I was also really, insanely unpopular.

1777
01:25:38,133 --> 01:25:41,177
And I had that exact situation play out
for me so many times.

1778
01:25:41,261 --> 01:25:44,264
I'd like to sincerely ask one thing
of those in Jae-seo's life.

1779
01:25:44,347 --> 01:25:45,932
I'm not joking here. I'm being earnest.

1780
01:25:46,015 --> 01:25:49,102
My friends also didn't tell me
the real reason I was unpopular

1781
01:25:49,185 --> 01:25:51,813
because they didn't want
to hurt my feelings.

1782
01:25:51,896 --> 01:25:53,731
And, you know, that didn't help.

1783
01:25:53,815 --> 01:25:54,941
- Mm-hmm.
- I'm lucky.

1784
01:25:55,024 --> 01:25:58,027
There came a point where my friends
started being honest with me.

1785
01:25:58,111 --> 01:26:00,572
- Oh.
- "You're a bit fat."

1786
01:26:02,448 --> 01:26:05,368
"And why do you keep
going around in a buzz cut?"

1787
01:26:05,451 --> 01:26:07,453
Oh, so they gave you
a really detailed rundown.

1788
01:26:07,537 --> 01:26:11,791
And once one person got through to me,
eight, nine people just…

1789
01:26:11,875 --> 01:26:14,169
Oh, wow.
So they really started laying into you.

1790
01:26:14,252 --> 01:26:17,672
But if you keep hearing this over
and over, it doesn't feel great.

1791
01:26:17,755 --> 01:26:20,383
- Mm-hmm.
- But Jae-seo is such a strong-willed man.

1792
01:26:20,466 --> 01:26:23,303
- That's right.
- Someone who's built a career like that…

1793
01:26:23,386 --> 01:26:24,387
Can accomplish great things.

1794
01:26:24,470 --> 01:26:26,848
Oh, they can do anything
they set their mind to. So cheer up.

1795
01:26:26,931 --> 01:26:28,641
- You got this!
- You got this.

1796
01:26:29,225 --> 01:26:31,102
- Hello.
- Everyone's here.

1797
01:26:31,186 --> 01:26:33,438
- Wow.
- What's this?

1798
01:26:33,521 --> 01:26:36,274
- It's sashimi, sashimi.
- Oh, my God!

1799
01:26:39,068 --> 01:26:41,070
Oh, my God. I'm so happy.

1800
01:26:41,154 --> 01:26:42,947
Thank you for the food!

1801
01:26:43,031 --> 01:26:44,657
Thank you for the food.

1802
01:26:44,741 --> 01:26:47,327
- That's the real deal.
- They're really digging in.

1803
01:26:47,410 --> 01:26:48,369
Mmm!

1804
01:26:48,453 --> 01:26:51,039
- Mmm. It's so good.
- It's so delicious.

1805
01:26:52,165 --> 01:26:53,249
God, that looks good.

1806
01:26:53,333 --> 01:26:55,084
- Can you pass that?
- I brushed my teeth.

1807
01:26:55,168 --> 01:26:56,669
- It's good, right?
- Why?

1808
01:26:57,754 --> 01:26:58,880
That looks so good.

1809
01:26:58,963 --> 01:27:00,715
I'm not sure about Jeju Island food.

1810
01:27:00,798 --> 01:27:01,633
So good.

1811
01:27:01,716 --> 01:27:07,472
I've never been in a group of 12 people
where I'm the only one drinking.

1812
01:27:07,555 --> 01:27:09,390
It's a first for me.

1813
01:27:09,474 --> 01:27:11,100
Oh, I would be joining you
if not for the meds.

1814
01:27:11,184 --> 01:27:12,769
- Oh, you went to the hospital today.
- Uh-huh.

1815
01:27:12,852 --> 01:27:14,771
You have to have soju with sashimi.

1816
01:27:14,854 --> 01:27:16,898
I mean, no one's had a single drink.

1817
01:27:16,981 --> 01:27:18,107
But my plate's empty.

1818
01:27:18,191 --> 01:27:20,610
My drinking snacks are all gone.

1819
01:27:20,693 --> 01:27:23,488
- Wait. Just wait until tomorrow. Uh-huh.
- Oh, really? Okay, okay.

1820
01:27:25,740 --> 01:27:27,283
Ah, now they're…

1821
01:27:33,164 --> 01:27:36,292
For a start, I'm quite certain
that he went on a date with Han-ju,

1822
01:27:36,376 --> 01:27:39,462
because he hasn't made eye contact
with me once today

1823
01:27:39,545 --> 01:27:41,214
since coming back from the date.

1824
01:27:41,297 --> 01:27:42,674
So I'm like, "What's gotten into him?"

1825
01:27:42,757 --> 01:27:45,051
- Really?
- Uh-huh, I do drink usually.

1826
01:27:45,134 --> 01:27:47,637
- Then please make a quick recovery.
- I should.

1827
01:27:49,889 --> 01:27:51,975
But he made a lot
of eye contact with Han-ju.

1828
01:27:52,058 --> 01:27:54,686
- They're sitting right next to each other.
- Oh, boy…

1829
01:27:54,769 --> 01:27:56,479
I'm on shaky ground.

1830
01:27:57,855 --> 01:28:00,358
Is he going to keep
closing his heart off to her like this?

1831
01:28:00,441 --> 01:28:01,901
It's delicious.

1832
01:28:03,903 --> 01:28:05,113
This is good.

1833
01:28:08,783 --> 01:28:11,828
The vibe is not good.
Everyone's got too much on their mind.

1834
01:28:11,911 --> 01:28:14,080
Today is a day
when everyone has a lot on their mind.

1835
01:28:14,163 --> 01:28:16,833
That's how it is
on the fourth day. Day four, baby.

1836
01:28:20,670 --> 01:28:23,047
Did you guys all struggle
on your dates today?

1837
01:28:24,966 --> 01:28:27,176
Hyun-seo's behaving
like she's just got dumped.

1838
01:28:27,260 --> 01:28:30,096
- She has zero appetite.
- Of course she'd feel that way.

1839
01:28:30,179 --> 01:28:32,598
- I guess.
- I was struggling a little.

1840
01:28:32,682 --> 01:28:34,600
There were two people I had in mind.

1841
01:28:34,684 --> 01:28:37,729
And once I was picked by one of them,
I started to want more.

1842
01:28:38,313 --> 01:28:39,897
I kept thinking of one person.

1843
01:28:39,981 --> 01:28:43,568
The fact that she hadn't picked me
made me lose myself in my thoughts.

1844
01:28:43,651 --> 01:28:46,112
WHO IS ON YOUR MIND RIGHT NOW?

1845
01:28:46,696 --> 01:28:48,823
Uh, it was Han Su-ji.

1846
01:28:49,741 --> 01:28:52,744
- Whoa, is today the day of awakenings?
- I know, right?

1847
01:28:55,079 --> 01:28:58,124
Uh, I thought it would be nice
if Su-ji picked me.

1848
01:28:59,167 --> 01:29:02,795
But, um, the fact that I didn't make
her top two today bothered me a little

1849
01:29:02,879 --> 01:29:05,256
and made me feel a little disappointed.

1850
01:29:05,340 --> 01:29:07,091
Finding out everyone's
top and second picks…

1851
01:29:07,175 --> 01:29:08,259
Made things worse!

1852
01:29:08,343 --> 01:29:11,721
I felt really heavy-hearted
after our date.

1853
01:29:12,555 --> 01:29:17,518
I'm disappointed that I wasn't able to,
uh, open my heart to her first.

1854
01:29:18,269 --> 01:29:22,732
And in that regard, I really need to show
some more initiative going forward.

1855
01:29:22,815 --> 01:29:24,817
I'm sure he has a lot on his mind.

1856
01:29:29,864 --> 01:29:32,700
By that point, the only thing on my mind…

1857
01:29:34,035 --> 01:29:37,497
was who Su-ji could have
gone on a date with.

1858
01:29:38,414 --> 01:29:40,208
Especially since
he confessed his feelings.

1859
01:29:40,291 --> 01:29:43,086
Wow, everyone's brains
must've been so busy. They're so quiet.

1860
01:29:43,169 --> 01:29:44,420
So refreshing.

1861
01:29:51,552 --> 01:29:52,929
I'm so exhausted.

1862
01:29:53,012 --> 01:29:55,139
- I need another drink.
- Can we talk outside?

1863
01:29:55,223 --> 01:29:56,099
Um, uh-huh.

1864
01:29:56,182 --> 01:29:59,644
- What could this be?
- Oh, Jin-woo's bothered.

1865
01:29:59,727 --> 01:30:01,354
Oh, a club?

1866
01:30:02,438 --> 01:30:03,731
A band club.

1867
01:30:03,815 --> 01:30:06,526
- His ears are peeled. Jung-yun.
- Oh, Jung-yun too.

1868
01:30:07,735 --> 01:30:08,820
I kind of, hmm…

1869
01:30:08,903 --> 01:30:11,614
I also have something I'd like to say.

1870
01:30:11,697 --> 01:30:13,366
You know, you asked me yesterday

1871
01:30:13,449 --> 01:30:15,618
if I was kind of
romantically attracted to you?

1872
01:30:15,701 --> 01:30:16,702
Mm-hmm.

1873
01:30:17,328 --> 01:30:19,372
I had never really thought about it,

1874
01:30:19,455 --> 01:30:23,459
but I felt like you were asking
for confirmation out of the blue.

1875
01:30:23,543 --> 01:30:27,004
So I think I kind of panicked
and said, "Uh-huh, that's right."

1876
01:30:27,088 --> 01:30:28,548
But I kind of…

1877
01:30:28,631 --> 01:30:32,093
I kind of misspoke,
so I've been feeling bad about it.

1878
01:30:32,176 --> 01:30:33,511
- Oh, really?
- Uh-huh.

1879
01:30:35,680 --> 01:30:40,143
I can't really tell right now
if I'm attracted to you or not.

1880
01:30:40,226 --> 01:30:41,853
I'll be honest with you,

1881
01:30:41,936 --> 01:30:43,604
I'm not sure right now.

1882
01:30:47,525 --> 01:30:51,028
But that doesn't mean
I don't like you or anything.

1883
01:30:51,112 --> 01:30:53,448
I hope you understand what I'm saying.

1884
01:30:53,948 --> 01:30:54,907
- Uh-huh.
- Mm-hmm.

1885
01:30:55,950 --> 01:30:57,702
I just don't know.

1886
01:31:04,917 --> 01:31:10,214
Honestly, as I was
making the rounds today, I just…

1887
01:31:12,842 --> 01:31:16,012
Actually, all my attention
was focused on you.

1888
01:31:16,095 --> 01:31:17,555
Mm-hmm.

1889
01:31:19,724 --> 01:31:21,809
And, uh, to be totally honest,

1890
01:31:21,893 --> 01:31:25,188
today's experience
just kind of confirmed my feelings.

1891
01:31:25,271 --> 01:31:26,772
Mm-hmm.

1892
01:31:26,856 --> 01:31:28,941
I don't think my top pick

1893
01:31:29,901 --> 01:31:32,570
is going to change from now on.

1894
01:31:35,531 --> 01:31:38,409
All day today,
I couldn't stop thinking about

1895
01:31:38,493 --> 01:31:41,787
who else you might be spending time with.

1896
01:31:41,871 --> 01:31:43,164
Mm-hmm.

1897
01:31:43,998 --> 01:31:45,917
- So…
- Mmm.

1898
01:31:46,501 --> 01:31:50,004
…that's why I think
what I'm feeling is romantic attraction.

1899
01:31:50,546 --> 01:31:52,381
- Because it keeps bothering me.
- Mm-hmm.

1900
01:31:52,965 --> 01:31:55,885
That's why I thought
that this was that kind of emotion.

1901
01:31:55,968 --> 01:31:56,969
Mm-hmm.

1902
01:32:00,473 --> 01:32:01,891
In my experience,

1903
01:32:03,017 --> 01:32:04,352
even on blind dates,

1904
01:32:04,435 --> 01:32:08,481
when I meet someone
for the second time after the first date,

1905
01:32:08,564 --> 01:32:11,817
I always kind of found
the other person slightly…

1906
01:32:13,402 --> 01:32:16,113
tiresome and didn't really
want to see them again.

1907
01:32:16,197 --> 01:32:17,031
Really?

1908
01:32:17,114 --> 01:32:18,699
But when it came to Su-ji,

1909
01:32:18,783 --> 01:32:20,576
even though we spent
so much time together,

1910
01:32:20,660 --> 01:32:22,286
I kept wanting to see her again.

1911
01:32:22,995 --> 01:32:25,206
Since this is the first time
I'm feeling this way,

1912
01:32:25,790 --> 01:32:29,460
I felt like I was
romantically attracted to her.

1913
01:32:29,544 --> 01:32:33,923
And also the fact
that it kept bothering me.

1914
01:32:35,675 --> 01:32:39,345
I think that's what convinced me further.

1915
01:32:41,472 --> 01:32:44,725
I just wanted to tell you how I feel.

1916
01:32:44,809 --> 01:32:49,021
What I wanted at this time is
for you to know how you affect me.

1917
01:32:50,273 --> 01:32:51,440
- And…
- Mm-hmm.

1918
01:32:53,484 --> 01:32:56,404
- …you don't have to tell me anything.
- Okay, I'll just keep that in…

1919
01:32:56,487 --> 01:33:00,866
I… I just wanted to be honest
about my deep feelings.

1920
01:33:00,950 --> 01:33:02,827
Okay. Thank you for telling me that.

1921
01:33:03,661 --> 01:33:04,996
- Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

1922
01:33:07,039 --> 01:33:08,040
Uh-huh.

1923
01:33:10,501 --> 01:33:11,919
- Kind of…
- Okay.

1924
01:33:15,089 --> 01:33:17,675
Man, Seung-hyun was so cool and calm.

1925
01:33:17,758 --> 01:33:21,637
Out of all the things Seung-hyun's said
so far, this was by far the most coherent.

1926
01:33:21,721 --> 01:33:23,556
- The way he spoke…
- Right, he didn't even stutter.

1927
01:33:23,639 --> 01:33:25,850
It was very clear and articulate.
He did great.

1928
01:33:25,933 --> 01:33:28,519
- I love it so much.
- "I just want you to know that I like you.

1929
01:33:28,603 --> 01:33:31,689
That's all I'm saying,
and what you do is up to you." So chill.

1930
01:33:32,273 --> 01:33:33,941
Just so classy and cool.

1931
01:33:34,025 --> 01:33:35,985
I'm here for it. I think he did great.

1932
01:33:36,068 --> 01:33:38,738
For a second there, he looked upset,
and I felt my blood pressure spike.

1933
01:33:38,821 --> 01:33:40,573
- Right?
- If that's how he'd left it…

1934
01:33:40,656 --> 01:33:43,034
- Yeah.
- …it would have been a bit, well…

1935
01:33:43,117 --> 01:33:44,994
It would have been awkward
for Su-ji for sure,

1936
01:33:45,077 --> 01:33:46,329
but he wrapped things up well.

1937
01:33:46,412 --> 01:33:48,414
- That was so cool.
- Cool, cool, cool.

1938
01:33:49,165 --> 01:33:51,125
Today's a good day to drink.

1939
01:33:52,335 --> 01:33:55,087
- Want me to grab a cup? Mix it with that…
- No, I'll drink it like this.

1940
01:33:55,921 --> 01:33:57,798
Jin-woo, what? Where is this coming from?

1941
01:33:58,466 --> 01:34:01,385
He's a lightweight,
but he's using a tall glass? Whoa!

1942
01:34:01,469 --> 01:34:03,054
That's too much. That's strong stuff.

1943
01:34:03,137 --> 01:34:05,431
- He's chugging.
- Oh, man, pour me another.

1944
01:34:05,514 --> 01:34:07,350
- Oh, you're here.
- Hi.

1945
01:34:07,433 --> 01:34:09,101
I think I should have a drink.

1946
01:34:09,685 --> 01:34:13,439
I'd be willing to bet it's because
Su-ji asked to see Seung-hyun.

1947
01:34:14,106 --> 01:34:15,941
But, uh, seriously, what's bothering you?

1948
01:34:16,025 --> 01:34:18,611
So, there were two people

1949
01:34:18,694 --> 01:34:22,615
that I wanted to approach
and get close to.

1950
01:34:24,075 --> 01:34:25,951
And to be honest,
before I went on the date,

1951
01:34:26,035 --> 01:34:28,954
all I hoped for was to get picked
by even just one of them.

1952
01:34:29,038 --> 01:34:31,832
But once I got picked…
once I got picked by someone I liked,

1953
01:34:31,916 --> 01:34:33,334
I started to want more.

1954
01:34:33,417 --> 01:34:34,418
I started thinking,

1955
01:34:34,502 --> 01:34:36,962
"It would be nice if I got to talk
to the other person too."

1956
01:34:37,046 --> 01:34:40,716
The thing is, she, uh,
didn't seem that interested in me.

1957
01:34:41,258 --> 01:34:44,470
But I just can't seem to give up on her.

1958
01:34:44,553 --> 01:34:46,097
It keeps bugging me.

1959
01:34:48,516 --> 01:34:51,977
I wondered if it was just a desire
to be liked by everyone,

1960
01:34:52,061 --> 01:34:55,940
or if I couldn't get her out of my mind
because I genuinely liked her.

1961
01:34:56,023 --> 01:34:58,150
But, uh, seeing her talk to someone else,

1962
01:34:58,234 --> 01:35:00,528
seeing that makes me even more bothered…

1963
01:35:02,071 --> 01:35:03,322
and agitated.

1964
01:35:03,406 --> 01:35:05,950
It makes me think, yeah, like…

1965
01:35:07,660 --> 01:35:09,245
it's because I like her.

1966
01:35:09,912 --> 01:35:13,040
Even if she rejects me,
I should at least talk to her.

1967
01:35:13,666 --> 01:35:16,001
Once the sword is drawn,
it's a waste not to swing it.

1968
01:35:16,085 --> 01:35:18,170
- That's it! Way to go, Jin-woo!
- We love a man of action.

1969
01:35:18,254 --> 01:35:20,214
Wow, this…

1970
01:35:21,090 --> 01:35:22,216
Oh, no.

1971
01:35:23,092 --> 01:35:24,593
I think you're right.

1972
01:35:24,677 --> 01:35:26,971
"If you don't do anything,
nothing will happen."

1973
01:35:27,054 --> 01:35:28,556
- Right.
- Jung-yun too?

1974
01:35:28,639 --> 01:35:31,183
- That's it. Yeah, that's it.
- That's it, Jung-yun.

1975
01:35:31,267 --> 01:35:32,935
- Oh, man.
- That's it, Jung-yun.

1976
01:35:33,018 --> 01:35:35,521
I hesitated a lot,
but I just have to go for it.

1977
01:35:35,604 --> 01:35:37,732
- Ooh, go for it.
- Let's go for it.

1978
01:35:52,913 --> 01:35:54,623
That's it. Straight to the gifts.

1979
01:35:54,707 --> 01:35:57,585
ETERNAL SINGLES' POST OFFICE

1980
01:36:01,130 --> 01:36:03,132
HAN SU-JI

1981
01:36:06,886 --> 01:36:07,887
- Wait.
- What?

1982
01:36:07,970 --> 01:36:09,346
- Oh, my God.
- Hold up.
